title: sausage casserole
directions: Cut crust off bread; butter on both sides.
Lay in 9 x 13-inch pan, covering bottom of pan.
Mix eggs, half and half and salt together; set aside.

title: hopping john
directions: Do not drain peas.
Bring peas and seasoning to a boil.
Stir gently.
Simmer on low heat 15 minutes.
Serve peas and broth over hot buttered rice.
If possible, prepare peas an hour or so before mealtime, then reheat when ready to serve.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs until smooth.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add sugar, flour, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: marylyn's tortillas
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, onions, lime juice and jalapenos.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Cut into 1/3-inch thick slices.
Cover with a damp cloth and refrigerate.
Dip in hot sauce when serving.

title: coney island chili dogs
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown beef and onion until beef loses redness. Stir in Hunt's tomato paste, water and seasonings; heat through.
Now, heat or grill hot dogs and buns.
Serve.
Place hot dogs on buns.
Spoon chili down center of each and top with shredded cheese.
Makes 10 chili dogs.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper in a skillet; drain. Add all the other ingredients; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls(an easy treat that kids love!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Eat.

title: bran rolls
directions: Combine shortening, boiling water, sugar, salt and bran in a medium mixing bowl.
Stir until shortening is melted; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to bran mixture. Add egg and beat well.
Add 1 cup flour and beat well.
Add remaining flour and mix well.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Punch dough down; divide dough into 24 pieces and shape into rolls.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in
a warm place (85°), free from drafts, until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
2 dozen rolls.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch in a bowl until smooth.
Stir in ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Freezes well.
(I always make two; one to eat and one to freeze.)

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Mix above ingredients together and put in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool Completely.
Can also be baked in 11 x 15 pan for 20 minutes for thinner brownies. Cool Completely.

title: miracle custard pie(makes 1 large or 2 small pies)
directions: In blender container, combine milk, eggs, sugar, flour, butter or margarine, vanilla and salt.
Cover.
Blend about 10 seconds or until mixed (do not over blend).
Stir in coconut.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool, then chill.

title: garden punch for 100
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ale, which you add immediately before serving.
Serve over ice mold.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Cook in a double boiler until thick. Stir continually. Add next 2 ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites.
Add remaining sugar.
Spread on top. Bake until lightly browned.

title: best chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour over chicken wings. Marinate
for
about
minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting every so often.

title: "kolokithia krokettes" - zucchini croquettes
directions: Mix zucchini with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out moisture.
Beat eggs; add zucchini, cheese, mint, flour and pepper to taste.
Shape and fry in butter over medium heat, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Brown both sides.
Makes 18, or 6 servings.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugars and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, oatmeal and M&M's.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: judy campbell's crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Heat in microwave or bake in 350° oven until warm.
Serve warm in hollowed out bread or with crackers.
Delicious!

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine broccoli and onion; cook according to package directions.
Drain well and add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° gas oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and spices until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Reserve 1 cup flour mixture.
Stir in oats.
Add flour and oats mixture to creamed mixture alternately with eggs.
Toss fruits and nuts with reserved cup of flour until well coated.
Blend applesauce and fruit mixture into batter.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple salad
directions: Boil together crushed pineapple with juice, sugar, egg, flour and cider vinegar. Refrigerate overnight. Mix with chopped apples, chopped peanuts and Cool Whip, thawed. Makes 10 servings.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup crumbs, onion, 2 tablespoons of margarine, salt and pepper.
Turn into casserole. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: holiday onions
directions: Cook onions in salted water until almost tender.
If onions have been cut in half, do not boil rapidly (layers should not separate).
Drain.

title: tom thumb squares
directions: Combine shortening, salt and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Cream thoroughly.
Add 1 cup flour and blend.
Spread this mixture in an 8 x 12-inch pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or less. Check when light brown.
Take out of oven and add 1 cup brown sugar and vanilla to beaten eggs.
Beat until foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons flour, baking powder, coconut and nuts.
Blend and spread over first mixture.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes until brown. Cool and cut into squares.

title: black cherry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use paper liners in 12 muffin cups. In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Toss 1 tablespoon flour mixture with cherries. Set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Cook pie crust about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, Karo syrup, milk, salt and vanilla to sugar mixture.
Add pecans last.
Pour in pie crust and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 pie.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: In double boiler, melt cheese and butter.
Add vanilla.
In a separate large bowl, mix together powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add to melted mixture and mix well.
Spray pan with Pam.
With your fingers, lightly pat fudge into pan.
Top with nuts if desired. Chill at least two hours before cutting.

title: cherry pie
directions: Cream together milk and cream cheese. Add lemon juice.
Place in pie shell. Spoon pie filling on top.
Chill and serve.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix until blended. Stir in crab meat, cheese and onions. Pour into 9-inch pie plate (no crust).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes and you've got it!

title: chocolate-applesauce cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Mix well; pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle last 3 ingredients over unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: venison swiss steak(serves 4)
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Pound and press mixture into both sides of steak.
Melt butter in large frypan, add steak and fry to a crispy brown.
Pour the rest of the ingredients over steak. Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: quick rising yeast dough
directions: Mix flour, yeast, salt and sugar together in a bowl and set aside.
Mix together in a saucepan on medium heat, milk, water and butter until scalding hot.
Pour hot mixture slowly into dry ingredients, beating with mixer while you pour.
Halfway through, add eggs mixing well.
Keep mixing liquid into dry ingredients. As dough forms, you may use hands (lightly floured) to finish mixing.

title: jello surprise
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix Jell-O, cottage cheese and Cool Whip all together.
Add fruit cocktail; mix together.
Chill and serve.

title: hot chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, salt and chocolate in saucepan.
Cook slowly until chocolate dissolves, stirring constantly.
Add milk; cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla. Serves 4.
Chopped, salted nuts may be added.

title: zucchini and tomato
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in corn oil until onion is clear. Then add stewed tomatoes.
Simmer until liquid is mostly gone.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Heat first 6 ingredients in a saucepan, stirring often.
Next, layer chicken mixture with tortillas (begin with chicken).
Add each shredded cheese to each layer.
Top last layer with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Set 5 minutes before serving (to ease cutting into portions).

title: austrian garlicky potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, cut them into quarters, put in a large saucepan, cover with water and cook until tender.
Meanwhile in a small skillet saute garlic in 3 Tbsp of butter until slightly browned.
Drain potatoes, add garlic mixture, cut in the remaining butter, add salt, pepper, and tarragon, and mash.
Slowly add whipping cream, mash until smooth.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 package of dressing over top.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: best-ever cake
directions: Stir well and place in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost when hot.

title: baked idaho-tomato potato
directions: Bake the potatoes at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cut in half.
Empty potato into a bowl.
Add salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons butter; mix.
Add the crumbled bacon bits, tomato puree and sour cream. Mix and add the shredded Cheddar cheese.
Stuff in potato; put under broiler to brown for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: louisiana broiled shrimp
directions: Place peeled shrimp in shallow pan and pour warm sauce over them.
Broil at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, turning once.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda and salt; blend into shortening mixture. Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop 2 inches apart from teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
(Do not grease if using a Teflon sheet.) Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: golden goodie bars
directions: Blend all ingredients together and spread dough in greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 1 x 2-inch squares.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Place fruit in large bowl.
Sift dry ingredients over fruit and mix.
Beat eggs until lemon colored and thick.
Pour over fruit.
Put in buttered casserole and sprinkle with topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrots in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain; add margarine.
Add salt, pepper, sour cream, chicken soup and all but 1/2 cup dressing.
Pour in casserole dish that has been greased with margarine.
Sprinkle with remainder of dressing and dots of margarine.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, eggs, sugar and 1 stick margarine.
Then add syrup.
Bake at 350° in 10 x 15-inch pan for 15 to 20 minutes (13 x 9-inch pan for 25 minutes).
Let cool completely.

title: punch
directions: Mix well. Serve cold.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Shake mix and potatoes together in a sealed plastic bag.
Bake according to potato package directions.
Serve while hot.

title: corn fritters
directions: Salt and boil sweet potatoes.
While hot, mash and set aside to cool.
Form around marshmallow and roll in corn flakes.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until marshmallows are soft.

title: hamburger pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 425 to 450 degrees.
In a large skillet over moderately high heat, about 300 degrees, heat oil and brown onion and pecans lightly, stirring frequently.
Add beef, drained mushrooms, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook, stirring frequently, until beef is browned. Drain off any excess fat; set aside and cool slightly.
Prepare biscuit mix according to pkg. directions for 10 to 12 biscuits. After kneading, roll out dough on a lightly floured board into a 15 x 12 inch rectangle.
Spread meat mixture along one of the longer sides and roll up in jelly-roll fashion. Pinch ends and seams with the fingers to seal well.
Cut roll into 6 or 8 slices. Places slices flat on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes, or until biscuit is golden brown.
Prepare mushroom gravy mix with reserved mushroom liquid and enough water to follow package directions.
Serve pin wheels topped with gravy. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the eggs, oil, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix on medium speed until very well mixed.
Turn mixer off and add pumpkin, water and flour.
Mix on low speed until flour is moistened, then increase speed to medium and mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 well greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool on rack.

title: herb sour cream dip
directions: Combine cottage cheese, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth (or whirl in a blender).
Stir in green onion, dill, garlic powder and sour cream.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat well.
Blend milk and vanilla.
Chill mixture for 2 hours.
Drain cherries and dry on paper towels.
Place bowl of sugar mixture on ice to keep cool. Shape into balls.
Shape small amount of sugar mixture around each cherry.
Place on wax paper; chill about 2 hours.

title: sausage and macaroni
directions: Brown sausage in oil.
Fry onion and green pepper in sausage liquid.
Remove 1/2 cup and save for topping.
Pour 3 tablespoons of flour into remainder of sausage and stir.
Add 2 cups milk and 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese and reserved sausage on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: simplest butter cookies
directions: Mix.
Make
into
balls.
Place on pan; press tops with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Mix together with bread crumbs and cheese.
Remove stems from mushrooms and wipe caps clean.
Stuff sausage mixture into cap of mushroom.
Extra stuffing can be placed on top of mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 - 25 minutes, or until mushrooms are tender and stuffing is browned.

title: french ham and cheese brunch casserole
directions: Make a layer of one-third of the bread, ham and cheese in a buttered 8-cup baking dish.
Mix flour and mustard and sprinkle 1 tablespoon over layer.
Drizzle 1 tablespoon of butter over and repeat to make 2 more layers.
Beat eggs with milk and Tabasco. Pour over the casserole.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour until puffy and golden.
Serves 6.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
While this is baking, melt caramels, margarine and milk, stirring constantly. Pour over baked portion.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over this, then pour remaining cake batter over.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Moist; no icing needed!

title: chilli sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in heavy pan and cook 3 hours.

title: skillet beef and macaroni
directions: Cook beef in large skillet until it loses its redness.
Remove beef from skillet.
Add macaroni, onion and green pepper to meat drippings.
Cook until macaroni turns yellow.
Return meat to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: painted sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs and vanilla beating well.
Combine flour and salt.
Stir into cream mixture.
Chill for 1 hour. Mixture may be divided in half and used later.
(Store in refrigerator.)
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Paint with Egg Yolk Paint.

title: caramel layer squares
directions: Step 1:
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Use low to medium heat so it won't burn; set aside.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together oleo, sugar and milk. Blend in flour, soda, salt, eggs and cinnamon. Stir in oats. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Chop onion, parsley, green olives and dill pickles.
Add to mayonnaise.
Add hot sauce to taste and vinegar.
Mix well.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a very large bowl combine soup, sour cream and garlic salt.
Add potatoes and Cheddar Cheese and mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Top with Grated Parmesan Cheese and bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 55 - 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 10 - 12 servings.

title: dad's peanut butter candy
directions: Boil milk and sugar until it forms a ball in cold water.
Add peanut butter; do not stir.
Take butter and grease down a pan, about 13 x 9-inch.
Put rest of butter into pot.
Wait until it cools, then stir peanut butter until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Let set and cool for 1 to 2 hours.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: orange jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add sour cream and pineapple. Put into a 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate.

title: english toffee
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil; butter and set aside.
Also line 9 x 9-inch pan with foil and set aside.
Chop almonds fine and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan; add water and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until peanut butter color, about 10 minutes.
Set peanut butter jar on stove for color match. Remove from stove and pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place half Hershey pieces on top and spread with knife.
Now use half almonds and press down.
Turn pan upside down.
Remove foil, rest of Hershey's pieces and almonds.
If foil doesn't come off, rub ice cube on foil.
Refrigerate until set.
Break into pieces.
Can be doubled, use bigger cookie sheets.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Wash whole cucumbers and pack tightly in wide-mouth gallon jar (glass).
Combine vinegar, alum, salt and pickling spice.
Pour this solution over cucumbers in jar.
Put lid on tight and set in a cool place for 2 weeks or more or can leave until a few weeks before Christmas.

title: citrus cooler
directions: Combine juices and extracts in a large pitcher.
Refrigerate until cold.
Just before serving, stir in sparkling water and pour over ice.
Garnish with fruit slice, if desired.

title: noodle salad
directions: Boil macaroni until done; drain.
Add mayo, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Chop up tuna and eggs.
Dice onions.
Mix all in bowl. Delicious when chilled.

title: refrigerated oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well the first six ingredients.
Then add flour, salt and soda.
Add other ingredients.
Form into two or three loaves, wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes at 350°.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix well.
Chill; let stand 1 hour.
Place in baked pie shell. Freezes well.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients except fried onion rings.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°. Top with onion rings and return to oven until onions are golden brown.

title: chicken-cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except sesame seed, chill.
Prepare sesame seed by baking at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll chicken ball in sesame seed.

title: fresh sausage(canned)
directions: Mix the meat and seasonings thoroughly. Shape into balls the size of a golf ball. Fry in hot shortening until done.
Place in hot, dry sterile jars and seal.

title: alex's favorite mushrooms
directions: Combine butter and oil in frying pan.
Cook mushrooms slowly. Sprinkle with onion salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Add wine; cover.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and serve.
Serves 6.

title: tubetini salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool.
Cook pudding; cool.
Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix all ingredients with Cool Whip and chill.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach, broccoli and pepperoni bread
directions: Sift flour into large mixing bowl.
Make a tunnel as to add 1 beaten egg, yeast and salt.
Gradually add water and work in good with hands.
Let dough rise in bowl covered with kitchen towel 3 to 4 hours.

title: cheesy macaroni
directions: Bring a large pot of water with a dash of salt to a boil.
Add a little oil to prevent macaroni from sticking.
While water is getting ready, brown the hamburger in skillet, adding the diced onion.
When water reaches boiling, start cooking macaroni as long as directions on box suggest (usually about 8 to 12 minutes). When macaroni is done, drain well.
When hamburger is ready, drain well. Dump all ingredients into a large casserole dish or baking pan.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Wonderful! Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mexican burrito pie
directions: Combine beans, biscuit mix and water in a medium bowl; mix well.
Spoon bean mixture into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate to form a pie shell.
Set pie shell aside.
Cook ground beef until browned, stirring occasionally to crumble; drain well.
Spoon meat over bean mixture; top with salsa.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges; serve immediately.
Dollop with sour cream.

title: sangria
directions: Cut the fruit into quarters.
Put all the ingredients into a large container (at least 1 gallon) and let it sit for 3 to 5 days.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour.

title: creamy cranberry frappe
directions: Combine milk, ice cream, cranberry juice, orange juice and ice cubes in an electric blender.
Whirl until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 3/4 cups or 4 punch cup servings.

title: east indian meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, salt, pepper, curry, garlic, eggs, onion, apples and orange juice together in bowl.
With hands shape into loaf and place in a shallow baking pan lined with foil.
Chill.
Loaf may be done ahead to this point.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 425° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into fine crumbs (1 1/2 cups).
Sift powdered sugar, cocoa and salt.
Cream butter.
Add to mixture with egg yolks.
Beat well.
Fold in beaten egg whites; add nuts and vanilla.
Put layer of crumbs in buttered dish.
Add mixture and put layer of crumbs on top.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: super rice bread rolls
directions: Stir yeast into warm water to dissolve.
In small bowl, mix well the dissolved yeast, milk and egg yolks; set aside.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir yeast mixture into flour mixture just to moisten. Spread dough with light film of butter to prevent drying.
Cover bowl with plastic and refrigerate overnight or up to 4 days.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can Durkee onions. Place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes. Unwrap crescent rolls. Separate into 2 rectangles. Cut lengthwise into strips. Place strips on casserole to form lattice top. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes until onions are golden brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and thickly slice apples.
Roll pastry out in a rectangle about 11 x 8-inches and 1/8-inch thick; cut into 6 equal squares.
Spoon 1/6 of the apples in the center of each square. Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon sugar; dot with butter.
Moisten edges of each pastry; gather up and pinch together, sealing the apples.
Transfer to 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine hot water, remaining sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Pour into pan around dumplings.
Bake in hot oven 450° for 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: almond iced tea
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Makes 6 (8 ounce) servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions. Drain. Rinse with cold water to prevent pasta from sticking together.
Drain well and set aside to cool.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars and homogenized milk in top of double boiler. Set aside.
Beat eggs and sugar well and add vanilla and canned milk.
Fold this into candy mixture.
Pour into freezer.
Continue filling with milk to about 3 inches from top.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chili beef-n-biscuit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large frying pan, brown ground beef, onion and green peppers; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except biscuits and cheese.
Simmer while preparing dough.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil until creamy.
Add eggs, molasses and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients sifted together.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Put in 3 or 4 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Remove from pans about 10 minutes after removing from oven.

title: lemon goodies
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and egg together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar; spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool well before slicing.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Cook until tender, not mushy, the beans, ham and water.
Add sauteed onion and butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: corn flake crumbs cheddar beef pie
directions: Saute celery slices in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Combine celery, cheese and mushrooms; toss lightly.
Spoon into hot meat shell.
Melt remaining margarine and combine with 1/4 cup crumbs; sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Return to oven; continue baking 10 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; then stir in chips. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.
Put nuts in bottom of pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan in rows.
Mix butter, sugar, pudding and milk until smooth.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with cloth and let sit overnight (unrefrigerated).
In morning, bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: triple orange delight
directions: Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions. Drain mandarin oranges, reserving juice.
Set mandarin oranges aside.
Bring 1 cup reserved juice to boil.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Pour into large bowl.
Add sherbet, stirring until melted.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: easy cream cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with creamed mixture with egg blended with vinegar and vanilla.
Shape dough into small balls and chill about 1 hour.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Mash down with a glass which has been greased on bottom and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Mix together salt, soda and flour and add to sugar mixture. Mix in oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Peel, slice and saute zucchini in oleo and chopped onions. Layer in large pan, well oiled:
1/2 sauteed zucchini, salt and pepper (sprinkle), parsley flakes, oregano, tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Cut steak into bite-size pieces. Put in casserole dish. Pour soups and waters over meat. Stir. Cover. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Remove cover last 10 to 20 minutes so sauce will thicken. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat.
Beat until creamy, adding more wine, if needed.
Place small amount of mixture on each slice of meat.
Roll up and chill.
Cut into 1-inch pieces to serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all juices and tea.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes minimum.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to package directions.
Cool and crumble fine.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients with mixer and pour half the mixture into a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all vegetables and toss well.
Add dressing and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Serve chilled.

title: wedding punch
directions: This is a good punch that is not too sweet. Great if there are any diabetics in the crowd. Vary the amount according to the number to be served, keeping the above proportions.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cream of chicken soup.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Then pour soup on top and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Grease muffin tin (cupcake tin).
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Mix will keep in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.)

title: hugs and kisses cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese with mixer until fluffy. Gradually add in condensed milk, beat until smooth. Add egg and vanilla, mix well. Toss chips with flour and stir into cheese mixture. Pour into crust and bake 35 minutes or until pie springs back. Cool and top with glaze.

title: banana split torte(no bake recipe)
directions: Mix 1 stick melted butter, graham cracker crumbs and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and 2 sticks butter and powdered sugar on medium speed for 10 minutes.
Pour over crust; then slice bananas on top, overlapping them.
On top of bananas, spoon on pineapple and top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries and nuts.
Chocolate syrup can be drizzled over top.
Best if made the day before needed.

title: connie sue's blackened pig
directions: Run the pig into the house.
Shut all of the doors.
Set the house afire.
Return in three days with oven mitt.
Search and serve.

title: baked pork chops with apple bread dressing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add onion and saut until lightly browned. Add other ingredients and mix well. Spoon into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Brown 6 pork chops in skillet. Place chops in single layer on stuffing. Salt and pepper. Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake about 15 minutes until chops are tender.

title: seafood pasta salad(insalata di pesca e pasta)
directions: Cook fettucine according
to
package directions; drain well. Combine
olives,
mayonnaise
and
yogurt.
Fold
in crabmeat. Whisk lemon juice,
oil,
vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper together.
Gently fold in avocado cubes.
Combine olive mixture with fettucini and
gently
add oil and vinegar dressing.
Chill and serve.
Garnish
with more olives.
Makes 4 to 6 servings as main course.
This is great on a buffet table.

title: emancipation proclamation breakfast cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400° and grease 9-inch pie plate.
Combine butter and sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Fold in blueberries.
Pat dough out to 1/2-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut into nine 3-inch rounds.
Place one in center of pie plate.
Arrange others around.
Spread with honey. Sprinkle with orange and lemon peel.
Bake 20 to 24 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine all the ingredients, except the dressing.
Just before serving, add the dressing and toss gently.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until smooth.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in milk gradually.
Add vanilla. Fold in topping.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze at least 4 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and melted butter; pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat confectioners sugar, eggs and butter for 5 minutes.
Pat over graham cracker mix.
Place drained crushed pineapple over sugar mixture.
Cut bananas lengthwise and place on top of pineapple.
Drizzle Hershey's syrup over bananas and cover with whipped cream.
Refrigerate uncovered at least 24 hours.

title: ham and green bean casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until slightly tender; drain. Spray casserole or baking dish with cooking spray or grease very lightly.
In a separate bowl mix soups together with Worcestershire Sauce and pepper.
Combine potatoes, ham and green beans in casserole.
Add soup mixture and toss to coat.
Bake, covered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and sprinkle casserole with cheese and french-fried onions. Bake for additional 10-15 minutes.

title: oriental express
directions: In a large skillet or wok, scramble eggs and set aside.
Heat oil in wok.
Add celery and onion and stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes. Add olives, mushrooms, peas, ham and eggs.
Mix well and stir in rice and soy sauce. Heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix until creamy.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Make into small balls and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: crockpot candy
directions: Put ingredients into 4 or 5 quart crockpot in order listed, cook for 3 hours on low. Do not remove lid. Turn off and cool slightly. Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper, let cool. Makes 170 pieces.

title: dessert crepes
directions: Mix the four dry ingredients together.
Stir in the milk, eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Beat with a hand beater until smooth.
Pour 1/4 cup batter in a lightly buttered 6 to 8 inch skillet.
First, heat over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook until lightly brown.
Cool on wax paper.
May stack them with wax paper between each.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain fat.
Stir in chili seasoning, beans and tomatoes.
Add water if desired to thin chili. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: 2 wiener supper
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese. Cook can of beans. Add long hot dog pieces. The liquids cause the hot dogs to curl.

title: date bourbon balls(makes 10 dozen balls)
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients except powdered sugar. Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Dip palms of hands in powdered sugar, pinch off pieces of dough and shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In bowl with electric mixer, combine sour cream, cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in slightly oiled 6-cup mold and freeze.
To serve, dip bottom of mold in sink of warm water until salad loosens itself and invert onto platter.
Decorate with parsley.
Slice and serve.
This salad should only be slightly thawed before serving.
Serves 8.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Mix and bake as directed.
Bake in 3 pans instead of 2 layers.

title: doodle cake
directions: Mix and pour into a large greased and floured pan.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: pineapple apricot hot punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes. Strain; discard spices and serve hot.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in a small amount of oil; drain.
In separate bowl, combine preserves, barbecue sauce, onion and soy sauce; pour over browned chicken.
Cover; simmer 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Add green pepper strips and water chestnuts during last 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Dip chicken breasts in butter to cover. Coat with Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, oregano, parsley, paprika, salt and pepper.
(Hint:
Put all dry ingredients together before dipping.)
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: crab bites
directions: Mix well and spread on English muffins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cut into quarters.
Serve.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Add onion and green pepper.
Combine remainder of ingredients.
Stir into vegetables until all are well covered.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: french chocolate delight
directions: Mix ingredients well and spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pat down and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, pepper and mushrooms in large skillet. Boil noodles per box instructions; drain water from noodles. Drain grease from hamburger; add hamburger to noodles.
Stir in jar of Prego spaghetti sauce.
In a 9 x 11-inch baking dish, layer mixture in bottom.
Add cottage cheese.
Layer remaining hamburger mixture; add cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together the ground beef, eggs, oats, bread, 1/2 cup ketchup, milk, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and paprika. Spread mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread remaining ketchup on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover; drain grease.
Return to oven.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until brown.

title: fruity yogurt spread
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients and chill.
Use as spread over rice cakes or a dip for fresh fruit.

title: corn flakes peanut butter squares
directions: Bring last 3 ingredients to boil. Pour over corn flakes. Stir. Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Cool. Cut in squares.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Combine and boil 2 minutes.
Pour in jelly jams.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients except the kidney beans.
Cook, uncovered, about 3 hours.
Add the red kidney beans the last 30 minutes.

title: orange slice bars
directions: Cut orange slices in small pieces with scissors.
Add to flour and salt along with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool the pan.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch bars.
Roll in fine granulated sugar if desired.

title: broccoli-tomato chicken(single serving)
directions: Season chicken.

In medium size skillet sprayed with Pam, cook chicken and onion until chicken is opaque, about 8 minutes. Add broccoli, lemon juice, thyme and other seasonings to taste. Cover and simmer for 6 minutes. Add tomatoes and simmer, covered, 3 to 4 minutes until hot.

title: cherry de-light
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate well before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Grease lightly and flour 9 x 13-inch pan; pour pumpkin mixture in pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Drizzle butter over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve topped with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Blend oil and sugar; beat in eggs.
Measure all dry ingredients and sift to blend.
Stir pumpkin into creamed mixture. Add dry ingredients.
Pour into wax paper lined, bottom ungreased, tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg together.
Add rhubarb sauce. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Bake in a buttered and floured pan about 9 x 11-inch for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm, un-iced, or frost with vanilla icing when cool.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and nuts.
Add flour and soda; mix well.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for about 1 hour at 300°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef in 1-inch squares and cook in olive oil in covered skillet over very low heat for 35 minutes or until tender.
Add a little water if necessary to prevent sticking.
Add mushrooms; cook 10 minutes and remove to top of double boiler.
Add butter and flour to juice in pan and smooth to gravy, adding the sour cream and cooking until blended.
Add seasonings; pour over beef and cook in double boiler 10 minutes.
Serve on rice or toast. Flavor improves with reheating.

title: fruit-flavored freeze
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in milk.
(Mixture will appear curdled, but will be smooth when frozen.)
Pour into 13 x 9-inch metal pan.
Freeze until icy crystals form about 1 inch around edge, about 1 hour.

title: 7 layered salad
directions: Place vegetables in layers in large flat dish in order given. Dab mayonnaise onto vegies by spoonfuls.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle with crumbled bacon or bacon bits.
Spoon out servings, do not toss.

title: gator ribs
directions: Pour off marinade, leaving a little in the bottom of the pan. Bake the ribs in a covered pan, 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Remove ribs from oven and put in clean pan.
Cover with barbecue sauce.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces well in shortening; drain excess fat. Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion slices, Chili Fixins and tomato juice.
Cover and simmer 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.
Remove chicken and slowly stir sour cream into sauce just before serving.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: barbeque pork
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Marinate 5-6 hours or over night.
Place meat on broiler pan with water in broiler pan to provide moist tender cooking of tenderloin.
Cook 1 1/2-2 hours at 350° basting with marinade every 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie a'la suzanne
directions: Roll crackers out to very fine crumbs.
Put sugar in bowl with crackers, add juice and rind.
Then add egg yolks, mix.
Pour into raw crust.
Bake in moderate oven until filling is no longer runny.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in margarine, add onions and mushrooms and seasonings, cook until tender, add cream cheese and milk. Stir until cheese melts.
Serve hot over cooked rice or noodles.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Mix the butter and sugar with a fork.
Add a little of the flour.
Turn the mixture out onto a board or a table and work the rest of the flour in with your hands.
Break off a small piece at a time and roll into a small ball.
Place balls 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Mash flat with a fork pressed crosswise. Bake at 250° for 50 to 60 minutes.
The cookie will be very light in color.
They are rich, but not too sweet and very, very good.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Press 1 package crescent rolls over bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Be sure all seams are closed (can put the roll between 2 pieces of wax paper and roll to size). Beat cream cheese, sugar and egg. Pour over unbaked crust. Press or roll out second package of rolls as before, being sure all seams are closed, then flip onto cheese mixture. Pinch edges together. Mix together the 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Brush crust with slightly beaten egg white so it will hold the cinnamon mixture in place. Sprinkle cinnamon mixture on top. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bar cookies
directions: Stir together.
Bake in a cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli sausage savory
directions: Press sausage into base of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover with sauce, broccoli, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with the bacon and cheese.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In a small bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Mix in corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt, then stir in pecans.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Mix in order; then fold in by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: sunday dinner
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put meat in roast pan.
Cut and quarter onions; put in roast pan and cover.
Approximately 1/2 hour check and see if starting to brown in pan.
Add 1 cup water.
Cook approximately 2 hours.
Depends on size of meat.
The last 45 minutes, peel and quarter potatoes.
Make sure liquid in pan will cover part of potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover. Dinner is ready when potatoes are done.

title: savoir-faire bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Chop onions and bell peppers. Combine cucumbers, onions and bell peppers.
Add salt.
Cover and let stand for 3 hours.
After 3 hours, drain ingredients.

title: taffy
directions: Boil first syrup, sugar and butter with vinegar.
Boil to hard boil stage.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased cake pan or cookie sheet.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Pull until white, twist into ropes and cut into pieces.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in baking dish. Sprinkle top lightly with additional crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° until brown, about 35 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: In mixing bowl combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles a coarse meal.
Remove 1 cup mixture and combine with cinnamon and nuts; set aside. To remaining crumb mixture add milk and baking powder.
Spread into a greased13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Sprinkle the reserved crumb topping over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cut into squares.
Garnish with whipped topping and a pecan half if desired.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until done; add next 5 ingredients.
Add as much Velveeta as desired; put crackers on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool slightly; add pineapple and buttermilk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: spiced oranges
directions: Cut oranges into 1/4-inch slices.
Simmer in water to cover for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain well.
Combine vinegar, sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a large pan.
Bring to boil; boil 5 minutes. Add orange slices; boil until clear, about 1/2 hour.
Good served with turkey, pork or lamb.

title: cocoa
directions: In large kettle, mix water and powdered milk together.
Heat so you may drink and stir in cocoa, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Makes 24 (8 ounce) cups.

title: lite vegetable soup
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan combine onion, broth mix, garlic, zucchini, carrots, whole tomatoes (mashed), parsley, basil and pepper.
Add 2 cups water and cook until vegetables are done, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Add Sweet 'N Low and salt to taste.

title: hot slaw
directions: Cook cabbage and drain. Keep warm. In a double boiler, cook egg yolks, water, butter, salt and vinegar until thick, stirring constantly. Add cabbage and reheat.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter together over low heat.
Add vanilla. In a bowl dump powdered sugar and cocoa.
Stir until blended. Pour cheese mixture into sugar and cocoa bowl.
Stir well until stiff and smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Pour over ribs in covered pan.
Bake at 350° until meat is done.

title: ham salad
directions: Put ham and bologna in a food processor or blender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Great on crackers.

title: crisp cookies
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together; set aside. Cream the butter until softened. Add the sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy. Add the eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition. Alternately add the dry ingredients in fourths and the milk in thirds to the creamed mixture, mixing until blended after each addition.
Chill dough for several hours.

title: ham and veal meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Place in a greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a deep baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour batter in center of margarine.
Pour can of fruit in center of batter (Do Not Stir).
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cold veggie pizza appetizers
directions: *Such as green or red peppers, tomatoes, mushrooms, cauliflower, broccoli, black olives, celery, etc.

title: lo-cal chili
directions: Cook ground turkey and seasonings.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: greek rice
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add cardamon, orange rind, butter, apple and raisins.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add to 2 cups cooked rice and serve immediately. Serves 6.
(Uncooked rice increases 4 times.)

title: tropicana fruit mold
directions: Dissolve orange jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water; cool until slightly thickened.
Fold in coarsely chopped apricots.
Pour small amount into oiled 2-quart mold.
Dissolve lemon jello in the 1 cup boiling water; gradually add mayonnaise to whipped cream cheese.
Mix well and add to lemon jello.
Add marshmallows.
Pour on top of orange layer in mold.
Chill.
Pour remaining orange mixture over molded layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili spaghetti soup
directions: Fry hamburger and onions; drain.
Mix all ingredients except spaghetti in large cooker.
Let simmer while cooking spaghetti. Drain spaghetti and mix all together.

title: homemade granola
directions: In saucepan, mix peanut butter, honey, oil, milk and salt. Pour dry ingredients and stir.
Add sauce mixture.
Pour into broiler pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir and bake 10 more minutes.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all together except crab meat.
Mix in crab meat last and put a little of the cheese on top.
Bake at 325° approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: gehakt(dutch meat loaf)
directions: Cook potatoes in microwave.
Peel and mix with hamburger meat.
In a square dishpan, add egg, salt to taste, pepper, garlic and nutmeg.
Add milk and mix well.
Cook for one hour at 375°. This is very good.
I suggest you eat this with steamed rice.

title: dad's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat all together. Add vanilla and whipping cream.
Put into can and fill to the line with milk.
Fruit or flavoring should be added before filling up with milk.
If we make this in the wintertime, we take the ice auger down to the lake and get two pails of ice and it works just fine.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly margarine, sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Stir in nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: magic cobbler
directions: In small bowl or pan that you wish to cook your cobbler, melt oleo.
In small mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and water.
Pour this mixture over melted margarine (do not stir).
Drain fruit and pour on top of mixture (do not stir).
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Fruit will sink to bottom; crust will be on top.
Any type fruit may be used.
This is not as good as a made from scratch cobbler, but it works great in a pinch.

title: garden sauce
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve over cooked vegetables.

title: egg custard or pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: swiss ham sandwich
directions: Combine mustard, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Spread buns with mustard mixture.
Place slice of ham and cheese in each bun.
Wrap buns in foil.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Use a medium size baking dish.
Put half package of crackers and then half the oysters and then another layer of crackers and then 1/2 can of oysters. Repeat until crackers and oysters have been used. Cover good with milk.
Put 3 tablespoons of butter on top. Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.
(Don't cook too dry.)

title: beef steak or roast marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Whisk to emulsify. Marinate poultry from 1 to 4 hours before grilling.
Marinate flank steaks and ribs overnight.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water until well done.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O; stir well.
Pour in jars or freezer containers.
Put on lids and freeze.
Very good!

title: philly pound cake
directions: Blend margarine, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla thoroughly. Sift flour with the baking powder.
Add alternately with eggs. Mix well after each addition.
Pour into a greased and floured tube or bundt pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: applesauce-nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon together.
Add nuts, egg, applesauce and shortening; stir until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers and melted oleo together.
Spread 2 cups of this mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pudding as directed with only the 2 cups of milk.
Stir in softened ice cream.
Pour this on top of the crust and chill for 1 hour.
Take out and spread the Cool Whip on top.
Crush up the candy bars and mix with the left over 1 cup graham cracker mixture and sprinkle on the top.

title: refreshing party punch(very easy!)
directions: Healthy and delicious!
Freeze strawberries in a Jell-O ring filled with water and a little cranberry juice.
Place frozen ice ring in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour in one part pineapple juice. Add one part cranberry juice cocktail.
Add one part ginger ale. That's it!
Party time! (Leftover punch makes a nice breakfast drink the day after.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Makes 2 pies.
Beat butter and sugar together.
Add Karo syrup and salt.
Beat.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie shells.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
After 30 minutes, cover with foil to keep from getting too brown.

title: butterfinger angel food cake
directions: Mix softened butter, powdered sugar and egg yolks with mixer. Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Slice cake 1/2-inch thick and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half of the filling over cake. Take candy bars out of wrappers and put in a plastic bag.
Crush with a hammer or mallet.
Spread half of candy over filling.
Then place another layer of cake, remainder of filling and rest of candy bars over first layer.
Refrigerate.

title: noble sugar cookies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt, set aside. In a large bowl, beat margarine, sugar and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla until well blended. Gradually add the dry ingredients, beating until well mixed. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm, several hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 375°. Pinch off about 1 Tbsp. of dough and roll to form 1 inch balls. Roll dough in remaining sugar to coat thoroughly. Place on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Flatten with the bottom of a glass. Bake about 8 minutes. Cool on a rack. Makes about 30 cookies.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350° or until light brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice for thinning sour cream.
Mix juice with sour cream. Mix all fruit with the sour cream mixture. Put into covered dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot for several hours.
You can double, triple or whatever for large crowds.
If in a hurry, start this cooking in microwave and then finish in crock-pot.

title: squash dressing
directions: Simmer both squash in shortening 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salt, pepper,
onion,
parsley,
soup base, celery salt, water and mix well.
Simmer 5 minutes more.
Add bread crumbs, soda crackers and
cornmeal.
Mix
well.
Add
the
beaten
eggs, stirring fast (or
the
egg whites will cook and you will have white pieces
in your dressing).
Cook a little more to thicken.
Also taste
to see if you need more of the ingredients or to add a
little
more water if the dressing is too dry.
Put into a baking
dish
and bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes to set and
have
a
nice
light brown
color
like your chicken dressing has.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter/margarine in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer next 6 ingredients.
Press gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Bring water, onion and margarine to a boil.
Cook broccoli. Add Cheez Whiz, rice and cream of celery soup.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place on round serving dish. Cover with chili sauce.
Sprinkle with crab meat.
Serve with crackers.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: tiny christmas cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line 3 dozen 1 3/4-inch muffin tins with paper baking cups.

title: rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients, then stir in enough white flour until dough is easy to handle.
If mixed in mixer, dough should clear edges.
Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.
Knead 5 minutes.
Put into bowl and let rise again for 40 minutes.
Punch down again, divide in half and shape into loaves.
Let rise 1 hour.
(If you use a mixer the rising time is cut in half.)
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: raspberry vinaigrette
directions: In food processor, process shallot, mustard and vinegar.
In a slow, thin stream, add 1/2 cup olive oil.
Slowly blend in remaining oil.
Blend in cream.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 1 cup.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo in skillet and saute onions.
Add broccoli and saute.
Add rice and cheese.
Put in casserole dish and bake until bubbly, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pastry for one-crust pie
directions: Mix flour and salt together in a bowl.
Cut in lard.
Sprinkle with water.
Mix all together.
Roll out on a floured surface. Put in a 9-inch pie pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 475°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine lemon Jell-O and hot water; mix constantly until syrupy.
Whip 3/4 of a large can Pet milk (cold); add juice of lemon, little at a time.
Milk will become very stiff; fold into Jell-O mixture.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; add to Jell-O mixture.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Pat some crumbs on top and chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 375° for 40 minutes in pie shell.

title: brown sugar peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together, cook over medium heat. Bring to rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add Marshmallow Fluff, peanut butter and vanilla.
(Optional, chopped walnuts.)
Use a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: last minute dessert
directions: Melt butter/margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan or whatever you may have.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine.
Throw in next 4 ingredients or layer.
Pour Eagle Brand milk (or whatever brand) over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, if you can get dressed that fast.
If not, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, melt margarine and stir in flour and salt until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add cheese; stir until melted.
Pour over macaroni and mix well.

title: puppy chow snack
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Place powdered sugar in a brown bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake.
Store in a sealed container.
A delicious snack!

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve the sugar in the lemon juice; add the pineapple and water.
Pour over a block of ice in a punch bowl.
Add the strawberries and ginger ale.
Serves 30.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Next add extracts, fruit and nuts.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours or until done.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice real good. Fold in pineapple, drained, real good. Mix well and pour in pie shells. Cover with Cool Whip. Let refrigerate overnight.

title: lime fruit dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, then add the combined egg white and sugar.
Keep in refrigerator.
Cut fresh fruit for dipping. Makes 2 cups.

title: peanut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to mixture; mix well.
Add rolled oats and peanuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grandma's cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add extract and blend in dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add raisins or pecans last.
Roll into small balls, place on a greased cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of glass which has been dipped in cornmeal.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make a hole and pour oil and eggs into.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 3 small loaves or 2 large ones.

title: baked chuck roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in roasting pan with lid. Sprinkle onion soup on top of roast.
Spread mushroom soup on top of that.
Add vegetables that you like.
Cover and bake 25 minutes per pound or until to your desired doneness.
You are about 5 to 10 minutes in the kitchen and then you are done.
It makes its own gravy.

title: grandma whitworth's applesauce cake
directions: Mix and set aside the applesauce and soda.
Cream together the butter, eggs and sugar.
Add alternately a mixture of flour, cinnamon, cloves and cocoa.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into angel food cake pan and bake at 300° for about an hour or until done.
This cake is better if it sets for awhile.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Spray an 8 x 9-inch pan with oil.
Mix all ingredients and pour in the pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of the tortillas in pan.
Layer with 1/2 of the chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients (except cheese).
Repeat next layer the same.
Top with cheese and corn chips, if desired. Refrigerate overnight or bake the same day. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place half of the stuffing in a greased 2 qt casserole dish. Saute celery, onion and broccoli until tender.
Add chicken, rice, cheese and soup.
Spread over stuffing and top with remaining stuffings.
Drizzle with margarine; cover and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and brown for 10 more minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in three layers. Ice when cool.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender at one time and blend until mixed together well.
Pour into a buttered 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, crust will be on bottom, custard in middle and coconut on top.
Let set for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add other ingredients and blend. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300 for 45 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: chess cheese pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool and cut.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add onion, soup and cheese.
Cover the top with the stuffing.
Slice margarine on top of stuffing. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Combine pretzels with melted butter and sugar. Spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400° and cool to room temperature.

title: quick green bean casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a skillet and fry on medium heat, stirring occasionally until sauce thickens.
Pour in casserole dish and serve.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust. Sprinkle with pecans. Refrigerate.
Stir pudding mix with milk at medium heat until it comes to a full boil. Remove from heat. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust.
Place plastic wrap on surface of filling.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and
ketchup with egg, hamburger and salt. Roll into little round
balls
and brown in frying pan. Mix
2 tablespoons flour in
pan
and
brown
to
make
gravy. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put juices in saucepan.
Add sugar.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of water.
Add to sauce.
Bring to boil.
Pour over fruit and mix well.

title: oven-roasted garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes into 1 1/4-inch wide wedges.
Combine potatoes, garlic, oil and rosemary in 8-inch square baking dish.
Season generously with salt and pepper. Roast until potatoes are tender and crusty, stirring occasionally, about 45 minutes.
Discard garlic; serve potatoes hot.
Makes two servings.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together in bowl and set aside, In large sauce pan or big skillet, combine oleo, water and Crisco and cocoa.
Heat until boiling, stirring to mix.
Remove from heat. then add flour sugar and salt mixture.
Stir just to blend.
All eggs, butter, milk, vanilla, and soda.
Stir to blend well.
Pour into greased floured long cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.
While cake is hot put on icing.

title: skillet potato dinner(super easy, super fast, super good)
directions: In a large skillet, cook frozen broccoli according to directions.
Drain and set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together 2 tablespoons of skim milk, cornstarch, mustard, basil and pepper.
In the skillet, stir the cornstarch mixture and remaining milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Stir in broccoli, potatoes, ham cubes and 2 tablespoons of the cheese.
Cover and cook until the mixture is heated through, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with remaining cheese before serving.
Makes 4 (1 1/4-cup) servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and gelatin. Add strawberries (thawed), Wesson oil, water and eggs.
Beat well. Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients, place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sunday meat loaf
directions: Season to taste.
Add enough water to form and shape.
Press into a sock and tie.
Drop into a large kettle of boiling water; boil slowly for 2 hours.
Set in cool place until Sunday morning, letting meat cool in liquid.
Remove sock and slice.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Combine black-eyed peas and remaining ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring mixture to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until peas are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: straw-ba-nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed until frothy. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Combine strawberries, bananas and pecans. Fold in whipped topping.
Add fruit mixture to egg mixture; stir gently.
Add food coloring, if desired, until mixture reaches preferred color.
Pour into freezer can of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Add enough milk to fill can 3/4 full.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions. Let ripen at least 1 hour.

title: baked beef dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter until browned.
Drain and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot with crackers, chips or breadsticks.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine butter and flour in a saucepan over low heat; gradually add chicken broth and milk, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Stir in chicken, salt, pepper, mixed vegetables and peas.
Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut into strips and arrange in a lattice design over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pastry is golden brown.

title: double chocolate torte
directions: Melt chocolate, then combine all ingredients but eggs in mixing bowl.
Mix well, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs; beat an additional 2 minutes.
Spoon 1/4 of batter into each of 4 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: danish puff pastry
directions: Mix the 1/2 cup soft butter, 1 cup flour and 2 tablespoons water.
Spread this mixture on cookie sheet in 2 equal parts, about 3 x 10-inch each.
Mix 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup boiling water and boil together.
Add 1 cup flour; mix well.
Add the eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add the almond extract.
Divide this mixture in half; spread across first layer.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Frost with powdered sugar frosting when slightly cooled.
(I add a little almond extract to frosting, also.)
Top with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies according to directions, allow to cool. Prepare mousse according to directions, set aside.
Crumble brownies.
Layer crumbled brownies, coffee (sprinkle on brownies) mousse, crushed Heath bars and Cool Whip.
Continue layering until all is used.
Garnish with crushed Heath bars.

title: toffee crescent bars
directions: *I use chocolate chips, butterscotch or peanut butter, together or separately.

title: homemade soap
directions: Cook until it becomes thick.
To test it put a little in a saucer;
if
it
is
thick like jelly when cool it is ready. Skim bubbles off top like you would jelly.
Then let it set and cool. When it
becomes firm mark off bars on the top.
Let set for 24 hours
and harden.
Cut out bars, wrap in paper, store. It will keep a long time, real good when boiling clothes.

title: dad's world-famous pancakes
directions: Re-sift flour with salt, sugar and baking powder.
Sift all together.
Combine eggs, butter and milk.
Mix liquid ingredients quickly into dry ingredients.
Cook.
Give some to your eagerly waiting children.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese together; will be stiff. Add 1 cup Cool Whip and mix thoroughly together.
Add vanilla; fold in remainder of Cool Whip.
This will make 2 medium pies or 1 thick pie.
Freeze and remove from freezer when ready to eat.

title: apple crunch
directions: Preheat over to 350°.
Place apples in 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples. Combine flour, brown sugar, and butter.
Spread mixture over sugared apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: creamed salad ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin into very hot cream of tomato soup.
When cool, but not set, whisk in milk.
Season well.
Pour into ring mold and when set, turn out.
Fill the center with green salad, shrimp or a diced cheese salad and mayonnaise.

title: sweet potato custard pie
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine; add eggs, sweet potatoes, milk and flavoring.
(Add flour with sugar.)
Makes enough filling for 2 pie shells.
Full unbaked shells and bake at 350° until set.

title: no-roll pie crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt directly into an ungreased pie pan. Combine oil and milk in a separate bowl; whip with a fork until completely combined.
Pour oil mixture over flour.
Mix with a fork until well blended.
Press onto the bottom and sides of the pie pan.
If a baked shell is needed, bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Place foil around edge of crust to prevent burning. Makes 1 pie crust.

title: munchy peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Stir together the sugar and corn syrup in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir in; microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and extract to syrup; blend well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot. Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Total cooking time:
8 to 11 minutes on power level High.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli squares
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 45 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add rice and shrimp.
Cook until heated.
Stir in eggs, beaten with the soy sauce.
Heat, stirring until eggs are done, along with green onions.

title: number one yeast rolls
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter, sugar, salt, potato flakes and hot water in saucepan.
Over low heat, stir to melt butter and dissolve potato flakes and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: grilled peanut butter & banana sandwiches
directions: Peel bananas and place in medium mixing bow.
Mash bananas with a fork.
Add peanut butter and mix together.
Spread on slices of bread and put together to make a sandwich.
Butter both sides and place in hot frying pan.
Grill until brown on both sides. This one is fattening...and delicious.

title: beer batter bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except butter.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Take out bread; pour 1 stick melted butter over top.
Return to oven; bake 15 more minutes.
Slice and serve immediately.
This is a one-step recipe.
All alcohol is cooked out.

title: chicken zucchini salad
directions: Cook chicken with salt until tender (could use whole canned chicken).
Cool.
Remove meat from bones; cut into bite size pieces.
Mix with scallions and squash.
Chill, while preparing the dressing.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Slice 2 lemons into very thin half slices.
Juice remaining 4 lemons.
Pour juice over sugar.
Let stand 2 hours in refrigerator. Mix with milk and half and half.
Pour into churn.
Add sliced lemons.
Freeze according to your ice cream freezer instructions.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and save liquid.
Saute onion in margarine; stir in flour.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese; blend until smooth.
Puree 1/2 of the broccoli in blender.
Slowly blend chicken broth in sauce mix.
Add pureed broccoli and whole broccoli.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pimento cheese ball
directions: Combine, blend well, cream cheese, cheddar and margarine.

title: leftovers in cream sauce over noodles(serves 4)
directions: Put hot water on for egg noodles and cook according to package directions.
Saute onion and mushrooms in olive oil until tender. Add sour cream, soup and milk.
Stir to combine.
Continue to cook over medium to low heat.
Add cubed meat or tofu and gently cook all until noodles are done, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add black pepper and paprika.
Serve over noodles.
Easy to double.

title: applesauce-sweet potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sweet potatoes, cut sides up, in ungreased square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Spread applesauce over sweet potatoes.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Sprinkle over applesauce.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake about 30 minutes or until hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Add all ingredients and mix.
Pack into well-greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: apricot tortoni
directions: Combine ingredients.
Press half of crumbs into 8 x 10-inch pan.
Spread half of 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt over crumbs.
Cover ice cream with 12 ounce jar of apricot jam. Top jam with remaining ice cream and then remaining crumbs. Freeze.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix oil, Ranch dressing and lemon pepper.
Toss with broken up pieces of pretzels.
I use a large plastic bag to toss.

title: chicken-noodle soup with vegetables
directions: Heat all ingredients, except noodles, to boiling in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Skim fat, if necessary.

title: churros
directions: Sift together the flour and cinnamon.
Heat oil (1 inch in depth) in large, heavy skillet to medium-high heat (375°).
In a medium heavy saucepan, bring water to a boil over high heat.
Add butter and salt, allowing butter to melt.
Remove from heat.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well with a whisk.
Add eggs, one at a time, whisking well.
Spoon into pastry or piping bag, fitted with star shaped tip.
Squeeze batter in a straight line into hot oil, making each Churro about 6 inches in length.
Fry until Churros are golden brown, about 3 minutes, turning occasionally.
Drain well on paper towels; sift confectioners sugar over Churros. Serve warm.
These are also sweet and delicious with a generous sprinkle of cinnamon and sugar.
Enjoy!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in saucepan on low heat until boiling (5 minutes).

title: salad dressing
directions: Cut all vegetables into this mixture and let marinate for about an hour. Add lettuce last just before tossing in all the other vegetables.

title: cholent
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Drain.
Put all ingredients in ovenproof casserole.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Remove cover last 1/2 hour to brown.
Serves 6.

title: snack crackers
