directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers. Toss crackers with liquid mixture. Pour into 10 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 275°. Allow to cool. Store in a plastic bag.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in bottom of greased pan.
In bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg.
Mix like a pie crust.
Pour over apples, then sprinkle a little cinnamon on top.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, salt, baking soda, egg and vanilla. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients and stir.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger, salt and chopped onions in the 3 tablespoons of Mazola oil.
Quarter the 4 potatoes and cook until tender.
Put these ingredients in a casserole dish and cover with mushroom soup.
Bake in a 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cheese may be spread on top, if desired.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place half of the eggplant slices in bottom of a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Place chard on top of eggplant; cover with the rest of the eggplant and pack down.
Next, place on the tomatoes, and on top, the onion slices.
Pour white sauce over the vegetables; sprinkle cheese on top.
Finally sprinkle on bread crumbs and dot with a little margarine.
Bake for 40 minutes or until eggplant is tender.

title: deep south pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well and combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: di's delight
directions: Place graham crackers on paper plate.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and marshmallows on top.
Place in microwave.
Heat until chips and marshmallows are melted.
Cool a little bit.
Mighty good!
Mighty messy!

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Whisk together the next 3 ingredients and add to dry mixture.
Stir last 2 ingredients by hand and add to mixture.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for one hour.
Cool on wire rack.

title: western corn-on-the-cob
directions: Combine margarine, mustard, horseradish, salt and pepper. Cream until light and fluffy.
Lightly spread over corn.
Wrap loosely in foil.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining mixture with parsley.
Serve with corn.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Stir shortening just to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add banana, milk and vanilla; mix until all flour is dampened, then beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes longer.
Stir in finely chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured pan (12 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish) in a moderate oven (325°) for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Mix in shortening until mixture
is
crumbly.
Add	enough	water
for dough, just dry enough
to work.
Knead lightly on a floured surface. Roll 1/2 inch
thick and cut.
Bake in greased pan (grease tops) for 12 to 15	minutes (until nicely browned) at 450°.
Sour milk may be used.

title: marinated zucchini and onion
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet and saute onion and garlic, tossing occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, cut sides down, in a single layer, over the onion and garlic.
Cover and reduce heat to low; cook until zucchini is tender, about 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato oil, wine vinegar and salt.
Pepper to taste.
Toss to combine and remove to a bowl.
Serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, peanut butter and sugars together.
Add the egg and beat well.
Sift the remaining dry ingredients together and add to the first mixture.
Add the vanilla and form into small balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet and press each ball flat with the prongs of a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo, then add broccoli and cook about 15 minutes.
While mixture is cooking, cook rice with water. When rice and broccoli are cooked, mix soup with milk and cheese and heat until mixed thoroughly.
Then mix all ingredients in a casserole and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix Hidden Valley dressing with mayonnaise and Tabasco sauce. Spread over top of vegetables and seal with Saran Wrap.
Let stand overnight.
Before serving, mix.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Sift flour and mix with sugar.
Melt oleo, cocoa, water and oil until they boil.
Pour hot mixture over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add milk when soda has been dissolved in it.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Mix well by hand; do not use mixer.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delights
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate until easy to handle.
Shape into berries; decorate with green leaf.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In an electric or heavy iron skillet, melt butter.
Add dates, sugar and eggs.
(After stirring in the sugar, remove the skillet from the burner to cool slightly, or you may have scrambled eggs in the date balls.)
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in Rice Krispies, vanilla, salt and coconut.
Form into balls; roll in crushed cereal, and they are ready to eat.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen balls the size of walnuts.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Make pudding according to box directions.
Make cake according to box directions, baking in 2 (8-inch or 9-inch) layer pans. Break up 1 layer and put in bowl.
Add half of the pudding, half of the Cool Whip and half the Heath bars in layers.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Best if served with a spoon.

title: barbara's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to mixture; mix well. Roll into small balls in sugar.
Press down with glass.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until brown. Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Stir together in bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir in milk, oil and nuts.
Spread in square cake pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in small amount of oil.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper.
Simmer meat and vegetable mixture.
Season with chili powder and salt to taste.
Melt cheese and add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cut lettuce coarsely and dice tomatoes; put in bowl. Add meat and vegetable mixture and mix lightly.
Add chips and hot hot cheese.
Toss together and serve immediately.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice; stir well.
Add strawberries.
Gently fold Cool Whip into mixture.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all together well by hand.
Serve with sliced Granny Smith apples. Yummy!!

title: easy peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut up margarine in baking dish; place in oven.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, milk and flavoring.
Pour in dish over margarine (do not stir).
Spoon peaches over batter (do not stir).
Cook in oven 1 hour or until brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco, butter and sugar well and add eggs, one at a time, then the vanilla.
Next add alternately the flour, baking powder and milk. Do not beat too much.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: aunt vicky's mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted, 25 to 35 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Butter the bottom of 10-inch glass pie pan.
Spread with coconut.
Place all other ingredients in blender.
Blend well on high speed.
Carefully pour over coconut.
Be sure coconut is moistened.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill. Serve with fruit. Yummy on a hot day!

title: nana's punch no. 1
directions: Mix all ingredients in large punch bowl and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until filling rests, baked, and pastry is brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with evaporated milk.
Add pecans; stir.
Add mashed bananas; mix well.
Divide equally into two 9-inch loaf pans, which have been greased and floured lightly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Add oil.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to eggs and mix well.
Fold in apples. Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: harvest nutty fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
(Do not brown.)
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Cook together in crock pot on high for 1 hour or on low for as long as you please.

title: hot spiced cranberry cider
directions: Combine all ingredients except lemon in large kettle.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove spices with slotted spoon.
If desired, float lemon slice on each cup.

title: tuscan bean spread
directions: Saut chopped onions until translucent.
Add minced garlic and continue cooking until golden.
Mix in cannellini beans and thyme leaves.
Cook over medium-low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour bean mixture into food processor and process until smooth, adding grated Parmigiano and 1 to 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Serve on baguette toasts.

title: peanut pattie
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Simmer for 70 minutes or until mixture forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla and a few drops of cake coloring.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased muffin tins.

title: hearty beef chili(serves 4)
directions: Scramble hamburg and onion in skillet.
Drain and reserve. Cook potatoes and celery until tender.
Strain, reserving water. Thicken water with cornstarch to keep veggies moist while baking. Put potatoes and celery in baking pan; add package peas and carrots.
Top with hamburg and pour thickened juice over all ingredients. Top with baking powder biscuits (I use Bisquick) and bake until biscuits are done.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Coat uncooked rice with butter.
Add onion soup, beef consomme and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: jellied chicken salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to hot bouillon.
When partially set remove half the mixture, leaving half in the serving bowl.
Arrange sliced olives over the contents and chill until partially set.
Stir pineapple, chicken and vegetables into remaining gelatin and pour carefully over gelatin already in mold. Chill.
Serve with mayonnaise.
Serves six.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients and pull stems off and stuff mushroom caps.
Drop a few spoonfuls of butter on cookie sheet and place mushrooms on it.
Bake for about 30 minutes at 350 degrees. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese when done.

title: strata(breakfast)
directions: Place bread slices on bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (spray with Pam first).
Cover bread with cooked pork sausage.
Sprinkle sausage layer with grated Swiss cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, half and half, mustard and Worcestershire sauce together and pour over top of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (tinfoil on top).

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix chicken pieces with sour cream, soup and 1/2 can of water. Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine the melted butter and 1 cup of water with the stuffing mix; top the chicken mixture with this (add only half of the butter if you use homemade stuffing and do not add water).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: blackberry nut cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: lunch box cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl combine margarine and shortening.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour and baking soda.
Stir in cereal, mix well.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Nuts are optional.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in salt and celery with enough boiling water to half cover chicken.
Add onion the last 1/2 hour of cooking.
Bone chicken, leaving
fairly large pieces.
Arrange in a 2-quart casserole dish; set aside.

title: cheddar chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Meanwhile in a medium bowl, toss cheese with flour and bouillon; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Be sure to grate cheese well.
This can be refrigerated and used when wanted.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, strawberries, oil and vanilla.
Sift together rest of ingredients, then mix all together.
Mix well.
Divide into 3 small loaf pans, lightly floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cook steak at 350° until almost done.
Add all the cans of soup.
Let cook until steak is tender on low oven, 300°.
Serve hot with whipped potatoes and rolls.

title: tostada casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce and the taco seasoning mix, stirring to mix well.
Line bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish with 2 cups crushed shells.
Spoon meat mixture over shells.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and refried beans; spread over meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and remaining crushed shells over the casserole.
Return to oven and melt the cheese.
Serve with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, sour cream and taco sauce.

title: cajun pork tenderloin with vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Rub Cajun seasoning into pork. Place in ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inches. Insert meat thermometer horizontally into center of thickest part of pork. Cut sweet potatoes and zucchini lengthwise into halves. Place sweet potatoes, zucchini and onions around pork. Drizzle margarine over vegetables. Sprinkle with thyme and salt. Roast uncovered about 35 minutes or until thermometer reads 160°. Loosely cover pan with aluminum foil and let stand 10 minutes. Cut pork into thin slices. Serve with vegetables.

title: beans so good
directions: Place beans in a deep baking dish, not quite filled.
Put thinly sliced onion and sweet pepper on top of beans.
Put biscuits on top of this in a circle and bake until hot and bubbly and until bread is done, about 25 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie(one 9-inch pie)
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water; dissolve over boiling water in double boiler.
Cool.
When cool, add both cremes.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add salt and sugar and continue beating until the egg whites are very stiff.
Lightly fold in the gelatin mixture, then the whipped cream.
Turn into the chilled pie shell. If pie shell will not hold all the filling, chill the pie 1/2 hour, then add remainder of filling.
Chill until firm; garnish with chocolate curls.

title: stuffed mushrooms(makes 8 to 10)
directions: Wipe mushrooms with a damp paper towel.
Carefully twist off stems from mushroom caps, leaving caps intact.
Chop stems very fine.
Place in a small mixing bowl with onion and butter.
Cook, uncovered, at High for 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is tender. Combine mushroom mixture with bread crumbs, hot pepper sauce and sherry; mix well.
Fill mushroom caps with this stuffing.
Place filled mushrooms in an 8-inch baking dish.
Cook, covered, on Bake for 4 minutes or until mushrooms are piping hot.

title: gourmet chicken seasoning
directions: Mix all and store in an airtight container.
Use for seasoning anytime chicken-like flavoring is needed (dressing, loaves, soups, etc.).

title: butter tarts
directions: Line small tart pans with pastry.
Sprinkle raisins in bottom. Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, corn syrup, vanilla and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture. Spoon into tart pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Place rack below center of oven.
Makes 24 tarts.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream in large mixer bowl the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and lemon extract.
Beat in slowly the flour. Fold in 7-Up.
Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: spinach, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and place in a buttered 2-quart ovenproof casserole with a tight-fitting lid. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is cooked through.
(Baking time may vary depending on the type of casserole used.) Makes 6 servings.

title: hot ham cheese roll sandwich
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in hot dog buns or deli rolls. Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cranberry topped brie
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
In a small bowl, combine cranberry orange sauce, brown sugar, pecans and brandy.
Mix well and set aside.
Cutting to within 1/4-inch of the outside edge, remove the rind from the top of the cheese.
Place the cheese on an ovenproof platter or glass pie plate.
Spread cranberry mixture over top of cheese.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is heated through, but not melted.
Serve with crackers or French bread slices.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into small balls and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherry balls
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, beating until smooth.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating until smooth.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased baking sheet and press thumb into center of each.
Place cherry in center of each cookie.
Combine chocolate chips and milk in small saucepan.
Heat until chocolate is melted.
Stir in 4 teaspoons reserved cherry juice.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon frosting over each cherry, spreading to cover.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Yield:
4 dozen.
These are delicious!

title: ground beef stew
directions: Simmer beef and onions in dry skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and cook slowly until vegetables are done. Serves 6.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut
peeled
eggs
lengthwise in half.	Slip out yolks; mash with
fork.
Mix in seasonings and salad dressing.	Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up lightly.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops over medium heat.
Arrange 2 cups potatoes in 2-quart casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 onion slices on top of potatoes.
Pour 1/2 can mushroom soup over this. Repeat procedure.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350° or until tender all the way through.
May double recipe for extra servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Drain strawberries and use enough cold water with it to make 1 cup cold liquid and 2 cups hot water.
Add liquid to Jell-O and let jell partially.
Add strawberries to Jell-O and spoon over preceding cooled mixture.

title: drunken roast
directions: You will need 1 Ziploc bag (gallon size).

title: deb's dilly dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Serve with vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: nova scotia fish chowder
directions: Cut fish in bite size chunks.
Saute bacon; brown until crisp. Remove and save for garnish.
Remove all fat except 2 teaspoons. In a large pan or Dutch oven, saute onion until tender.
Add potatoes, carrot and water; simmer until almost done (10 to 15 minutes).
Add fish and simmer 5 minutes more.
Add flour and water mixture and cook until thickened.
Add rest of ingredients and heat, but do not boil.
Serve hot, garnished with bacon bits.

title: spring broccoli soup
directions: Cut broccoli into tiny florets.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter; add onion and saute until tender. Blend in flour and gradually add chicken broth, stirring all the while.
Heat slowly until mixture boils.
Add the Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt, broccoli and milk.
Sprinkle in grated cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve garnished with fresh parsley.

title: dumpling noodle soup
directions: Cook dumplings according to directions in large pot.
Drain and put aside.
Open large can and small can of chicken broth and pour into large pot.
Add onion, celery and parsley.
Stir and add dumplings.
Let simmer- you might have to open second small can of broth.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Cook in double boiler; melt butter in pan and saute onion and green pepper for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Can be made in morning and reheated before serving. Serves 16.

title: old-fashioned new england bean soup
directions: In a large soup pot, soak beans overnight in water to cover or use quick soak method*.
Drain and add cold water, bacon, celery, onion and carrot.
Simmer, covered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until beans are tender.
Add salt and pepper and serve.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Put corned beef in a large pot covered completely with water. Place on low boil for about 4 to 5 hours.
During last 1/2 hour, put in the potatoes, carrots and cabbage.
Serve with fresh buns, sliced tomatoes and pickles.
Yummy!

title: banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas in cooled pie shell.
Combine sour cream and milk; blend well.
Add pudding and beat until thickened.
Pour over banana slices and chill well.
Cover top with banana slices and put whipped cream (Cool Whip) over all.
Store in refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch container that has been sprayed with Pam.
Place in freezer overnight.
Dice and serve.

title: lemon streusel coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve 2 tablespoons cake mix (dry).
In a large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs.
Beat at low speed until moistened, then beat 2 minutes at highest speed.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Grease a cold, large cast-iron skillet.
Mix all ingredients, except water.
If batter will not run off spoon, add water until it does.
Pour in skillet.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Bake cake mix in round layer pans.
Cool.
Tear one layer in chunks and put in punch bowl.

title: scones
directions: Sift flour and measure; sift all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender and finish working it in with the tips of the fingers.
Add milk and mix to a soft dough.
Knead lightly, cut in half, shape each piece into a round, roll out and try to keep in nice shape.
Cut in four.
Bake on a moderate griddle until evenly browned.
Makes 16 triangular scones.

title: honey sauce for fruit
directions: Combine honey and sour cream; add poppy seed, if desired. Just before serving fresh fruit, drizzle over individual fruit cups.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in 3-quart glass casserole dish.
Sprinkle on flour, salt and onion.
Pour milk over all.
Dot with margarine. Cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes. Stir, recover and continue cooking on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand.
Top with shredded cheese if desired.

title: b~l~t dip
directions: Blend together and serve with toast slices.

title: quick cinnamon bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Put biscuit pieces in a large Ziploc baggie with sugar and cinnamon; shake until all the pieces are evenly coated.
Put biscuit pieces into well oiled Bundt pan. Melt the margarine over low heat; add brown sugar.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Invert on plate and serve.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Line a 9 x 13 inch dish with half the mixture.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half of this mixture over crumbs.
Top with pie filling then rest of cheese mixture. Sprinkle with rest of crumbs and refrigerate.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix margarine and sugar. Add milk, flour and baking powder together.
Grease pan.
Pour in batter and pour berries on top of batter.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top of berries.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top. Cook in oven until brown at 375°.

title: surprise salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid, set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to reserve liquid to make 1 1/2 cups.
Bring to a boil, add jello, stir until dissolved.
Chill jello until slightly thickened.
Combine cool whip, pineapple, nuts, cheese spread and sugar.
Pour into 8 inch square pan. chill until firm.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix together tomatoes, onion and peppers.
Pour salt over all and let soak for 3 to 4 hours; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together and cook slow until thick.
Seal in jars.

title: texas chili dip
directions: Cook meat until nearly done.
Drain grease.
Add other ingredients; stir while bringing to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Serve with chips from fondue pan (or crock-pot).
If you want hotter, use "hot" picante sauce.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place in quart jars alum, garlic salt and dill seed.
Fill jars with whole or sliced cucumbers.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over cucumbers in jars.
Seal, then shake to mix.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend flour, sugar, salt and butter.
Add milk, eggs and corn. Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until firm and slightly brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray pan. Layer croutons, bacon, cheese and onions. In a bowl mix eggs, milk, parsley, salt and pepper. Pour on top. Bake in a 325 degree oven for 50 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, one cup at a time, to make a stiff dough.
Spread in pan to form a circle and flute the edge. Prick with a fork and mark 16 wedge shaped pieces.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
While hot, cut into 16 wedges as marked.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired.
Makes 16 pieces.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer macaroni, butter and cheeses in order given in a 9x13 dish.
Pour milk over the top layer.

title: easy granola
directions: Combine all together.
Heat liquids and salt.
Toast at 350° for 15 minutes, then turn down to 275° until golden.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add ham and simmer 5 to 10 minutes more until heated through.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: brian's alternate marinade
directions: Marinate chicken for an hour.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Marinade will keep stored
in
jar and refrigerated when using less chicken.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix egg and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to mix.
Carefully fold in blueberries, then stir in oil.
Spoon mixture into 12 paper lined muffin pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: totally awesome meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch or 2-inch meatballs and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: shawn's creamy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Let cream cheese sit out 30 minutes to soften.
In large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix very well, the better you mix, the smoother the cheesecake will be.
Pour mixture into crust and bake for 40 minutes.
Let cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and water or juice. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Add pineapple and bring to a boil again. Cook 10 minutes more. Remove from heat and quickly stir in Jell-O. Put in jars and seal. Makes 4 to 6 pints.

title: lemonade  pie
directions: Combine and fill 2 (8-inch) graham cracker crusts.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, butter and oil together.
Pour over the popcorn and peanut mixture.
Mix well.
Add the M&M's last because they will MELT!!!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat together vegetable oil and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas. Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture and add milk and vanilla.
Beat well and add chopped nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan (greased and floured).
Bake 1 hour or more at 350° until toothpick comes out clean from the center.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat and onions in margarine. Add other ingredients and cook until done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Meanwhile, put onions and oleo in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and brown in oven.
While these are browning, put water, soy sauce and beef broth in a boiler and heat to boiling.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over onions.
Add the liquids from boiler.
Add seasonings.
Place chops around in casserole. Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add beans and seasonings.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add meat mixture.
Mix lightly and serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: aprill family's sweet pickles
directions: Slice pickles 1/4-inch thick.
Quarter the onions. Slice peppers into thin strips.
Place all into extremely large bowl. Add garlic.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with salt, then ice.
Let sit for 3 hours.
Drain.
Set aside.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add chopped onion, salt and pepper. Cook until onions are done.
Combine meat mixture with soup; add cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with Tots and more cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a Dutch oven, except the noodles, and heat to boiling.
Immediately reduce the heat to simmer.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate. Skim the fat.
Remove chicken from stock.
Take meat off bones and discard skins and bones.
Cut meat into small pieces.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, brown sugar, salt and flour.
Beat in thoroughly the eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Add milk and butter.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites into a meringue sweetened with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread over pies and brown.
(Bake until firm.)

title: summer lime chicken breasts
directions: Trim fat and pound breasts.
Combine olive oil, lime juice, garlic, 2 tablespoons cilantro, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Pour over chicken and marinate 1 hour.
Grill or broil chicken breasts for 2 minutes on each side.
Remove to platter.
Sprinkle with remaining cilantro and serve with peppers.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: kahlua chocolate cake(an adult chocolate cake!)
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, sour cream, Kahlua and vegetable oil.
Using electric mixer, beat at low speed to blend, then increase speed and beat 3 to 5 minutes at medium-fast speed. Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 30 minutes.
Loosen from pan and invert, removing pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together the shortening, packed brown sugar and egg. Mix flour, sour milk or buttermilk and vanilla in separate bowl. Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in rhubarb.
Bake at 325° in 13 x 8-inch pan for 50 minutes.

title: halibut casserole
directions: Saut garlic in butter. Rinse and pat dry the fish.
Coat in butter mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Layer in buttered casserole; top with green onions.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Parmesan cheese with chives.
Spoon over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until fish flakes with fork.

title: microwave vegetable casserole
directions: Combine
butter,
milk,
eggs,
onion, salt and pepper. Mix well with a fork.
Stir in cracker crumbs and vegetables. Pour into a well-greased 5 cup glass or microwave safe plastic ring mold.
Microwave at Medium-high (7) for 10 to 12 minutes. Serves 4.

title: roasted tomato and basil relish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake until tomatoes are soft (about 30 minutes). Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy oven-proof skillet.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour mixture into the hot pan of butter; stir until heated.
Put skillet in 350° oven and bake until crusted around the edge and top.
Turn oven off and let pudding continue to simmer in the oven.
Complete cooking time is around 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, topped pudding or ice cream once cooled.

title: granny's tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well with hands.
Chill before rolling.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese squares
directions: Slice one pkg.
Of cookie dough, thinly, and place on bottom of 9x19-inch pan to cover.
Push dough down so it completely cover bottom of pan with no spaces.
Mix cream cheese with eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cookie dough.
Slice remaining pkg. of cookie dough into thicker slices and place all over top.
Bake in 350-degree oven for 30-35 min.
Cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini-crusted pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare a 10-inch pie pan.
Combine zucchini, egg whites, flour, cheeses, herbs and 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a bowl and mix well.
Spread into the prepared pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
About halfway through the baking, brush with the remaining tablespoon of oil.
Remove from oven and let cook for about 10 minutes.
Top with your favorite heart healthy pizza items and return to oven until heated through.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add salt and vanilla and mix well. Add flour in three equal portions and blend; add nuts and mix well.
Make into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with glass which has been dipped in powdered sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes; cover with powdered sugar.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour.
Cook until thick.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts and sauce thickens.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form a loaf in baking pan. Spread catsup over top and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian garlic toast
directions: Slice the bread lengthwise; place with the cut side up on a large baking sheet.
In a small bowl combine butter, cheese, garlic and oregano.
Brush onto cut surface of the bread. Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil about 4 minutes or until lightly toasted.
Cut crosswise into 3 inch pieces to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix tomatoes and salsa mix; set aside.
Brown beef well and drain off fat.
Rinse with hot water.
Return to pan and mix in taco seasoning and add a small amount of water.
Mix well.
Cover pan.
Simmer to blend flavors for 3 to 5 minutes, then uncover to let water evaporate.

title: macaroni and sausage
directions: Saute sausage with celery.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: southern style sausage stuffing
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions on Martha White cornmeal.
Cool, crumble and set aside.
Combine sausage, celery, and onion in large skillet.
Saute mixture over medium heat until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender; drain well. Pour sausage mixture into large bowl.
Add cornbread and remaining ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Stuff mixture into bird; roast according to standard roasting direction.
Mixture may also be baked in a greased pan at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown. Makes about 12 cups stuffing or 10 to 12 servings.
Will stuff one 12 to 14 pound turkey.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix all together, cranberries last.
Bake in greased and floured cake pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl; stir until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
While cake is cooling, prepare Chocolate Frosting.

title: orange pound cake(diabetic)
directions: Coat bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with cooking spray.
Dust with 1 teaspoon flour.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine orange rind, juice and oil.
Add to flour mix.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold 1/3 of egg whites into batter.
Fold in remaining egg whites.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Then cool on wire rack.

title: sugar plum cake
directions: Pour this mixture over the marble cake batter (cheese mixture will settle to bottom of cake during baking).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately in lightly salted water. Use as little water as possible to conserve vitamins.
Mix broccoli, rice, soup and Cheez Whiz together.
Season to taste. Put mixture into individual casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg; add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat well with eggbeater.
Sprinkle with nutmeg on top.

title: german vegetable soup
directions: Bring to a low boil and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Add cabbage about 5 minutes.
You may use frozen vegetables instead of canned.

title: mother's specialty
directions: Put dates, sugar and shortening into a bowl; over this pour boiling water.
Let cool.
Sift flour with other dry ingredients; add nuts and mix well.
Pour the first mixture into the flour and mix until free of lumps.
Add beaten egg.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: healthy ground beef casserole
directions: Cook beef in heavy skillet; drain off all fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake until carrots and cabbage are tender.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use any spices or herbs that you wish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mash and mix ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal and cottage cheese first and then the rest of the ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stove top scallop potatoes(no milk)
directions: Brown bacon and add onion until soft.
Add flour and stir. Add boiling water and raw potatoes.
Season with salt.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add bacon and 1 tablespoon Italian dressing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine other ingredients (except cracker crumbs) to make sauce.
Then combine with broccoli.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
This may be refrigerated or frozen before baking.
Serves 12.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, pineapple, juice and eggs all together until moist and place in 13 x 9-inch lightly greased pan. Sprinkle with pecans and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash lettuce; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble. Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper until sugar dissolves.
Add bacon.
Cook until hot.
Pour over lettuce.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken, salt and pepper until tender; chop and put into deep Pyrex dish.
Spread chopped onion over chicken.
Melt margarine; pour over chicken.
Bring to boil celery soup and chicken broth.
Mix flour and milk well and pour over chicken; add celery soup and broth mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not cook too thick.

title: thai yellow rice
directions: Cook rice for 30 minutes in water with salt.
Combine and bring to a boil next 5 ingredients and add to rice pot.
Bring back to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: merk's coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, singly, beating well after each addition.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Cook.
Melt cheese; cook rice per directions.
Combine all together and bake in oven for 30 minutes in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in frying pan until done; drain. Combine hamburger, onion, string beans, carrots and tomato soup in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Bring broth to boil.
Add rice.
Cook 20 minutes or until done.
Add all vegetables and artichokes.
Add artichoke liquid and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle on curry powder and mix well.
Chill.

title: clara and erna simon's "zwetschenkuchen"(plum cake)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Mix flour and yeast together.
Melt butter; mix in sugar, eggs, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Mix all ingredients together; beat until blisters form. Add 1/4 cup milk to soften.
Let rise 1/2 hour in warm place. Punch down.
Divide dough into 2 pieces.
Place each piece of dough in center of a pie pan and gently ease and flatten to pan edges.
Place plums on top in circular pattern.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until double in bulk (about 2 hours).
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes 10 minutes.
Cool and grate into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with minced onion.
Mix together mushroom soup and sour cream and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cube steak smothered in gravy(cooked in pressure cooker)
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Cover with flour.
Brown in the bottom of pressure cooker in oil.
After all pieces are brown, pour excess oil out of pan.
Return meat to cooker.
Add water.
Cook under pressure (15 pounds) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool pan by running cool water on top of lid prior to opening.
Excellent with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chicken spaghetti(12 to 15 servings)
directions: Cook chicken (boil).
After it cools, cut into bite-sized pieces and set aside.
Fry bacon in a large skillet until brown. Remove from pan all but 2 tablespoons grease.
Brown onions; add crumbled bacon, tomatoes, mushrooms and olives.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer for 10 minutes. Butter casserole dish and layer spaghetti, chicken mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until thoroughly heated and bubbly.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients in small crock-pot.
Cook on low heat until meat is tender (6 to 8 hours).
Stir only occasionally.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break crackers into pastry lined plate.
Combine in saucepan water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Boil gently for 15 minutes. Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot generously with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in 1 1/2-quart bowl on High for one minute; stir well.
Microwave one minute longer.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into greased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Refrigerate until firm; cut into squares.

title: down home rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Brown sausage and onion in skillet, then drain. Combine sausage, corn, Ro-Tel, cream of mushroom soup, Velveeta cheese, sliced mushrooms and rice. Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake in oven for 30 minutes. Remove dish and sprinkle top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Place back in oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: easy party chicken breasts
directions: Line greased baking dish with onion slices.
Lay chicken breasts on onions.
Sprinkle with Accent (just a little), salt and pepper (also lemon pepper, if you like).
Mix soup, cheese and fresh mushrooms and spread on top of each chicken breast.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be served with Rice-A-Roni chicken and mushrooms.

title: wheat muffins
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into a bowl.
Mix milk, beaten egg and margarine in a bowl, then mix with the dry ingredients and stir well.
Pour into baking cups and bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meatball and vegetable stew
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots 15 minutes.
Combine ground chuck, bread, salt, egg and 1/4 cup water.
Makes 18 balls.
Melt butter in a large pan. Brown meatballs. Remove as browned. Add onion and celery. Saute. Return meatballs. Add broth, Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 cup water and vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Gently fold water/flour mixture in stew. Cook until thickened.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, together and put in casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick butter, crumble up about 1 cup Ritz crackers and put on top of casserole.
Pour butter over crackers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheesy salmon rotini
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oleo and add small amount garlic powder.
Stir in flour, salt and dry mustard.
Add milk to reserved liquid to equal 2 1/4 cups.
Blend into flour mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Add salmon.
Heat through.
Prepare rotini pasta according to package directions; drain.
Add softened oleo and toss to coat.
Arrange on warm serving platter and spoon hot salmon mixture over the rotini.

title: swedish cole slaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, chopped green pepper, chopped onion, mustard seed and celery seed.
Set aside.

title: egg pie
directions: Beat eggs
well.
Sift	sugar
and flour together, then pour into the
beaten eggs and mix well.
Add butter and milk. Beat well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti rice
directions: In large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons oil over medium heat. Add mushrooms and onions; saute until lightly brown.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in skillet and brown spaghetti (be careful, it browns fast!).
Remove skillet from heat and return mushrooms and onions to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bring to a boil; reduce the heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Freezes well.

title: orange delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 10 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Chill can of sauerkraut in refrigerator overnight.
Drain juice; rinse kraut well in cold water.
Thinly slice radishes. Cut pepper into thin strips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and onion fine.
Cook until tender, then drain the excess water off.
Add margarine, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and herb stuffing.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle some herb crumbs over the top and bake for about 25 minutes or until it begins to bubble.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour and cream cheese; stir until smooth.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Cook broccoli and drain well.
Add to the cheese mixture.
Stir in salt and pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with croutons. Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in top of double boiler, add scalded milk and stir.
Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Beat egg yolks, stir into a little of the hot mixture and pour into mixture in double boiler.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add butter, vanilla and coconut. Cool.

title: peanut butter cup pie(low sugar)
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey. Heat 20 seconds in microwave or until melted. Stir in cereal; press into pie pan to form crust. Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
When thick, fold in Cool Whip, then pour into pie crust. Chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pan.	Bake at 400° until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Using an electric mixer, combine sugar, oil and eggs. Beat until light and fluffy. Stir in pumpkin. Combine dry ingredients and stir into pumpkin mixture. Add water and nuts, mixing well. Spoon batter into 2 well greased 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 min.

title: muffin crayons(use crayon recipe)
directions: When crayons become too small to use, separate the colors and remove labels.
Put separate colors in muffin liners.
For fun colors, mix the colors in one liner.
Place muffin pan in warm oven until crayons melt.
The "old" broken crayons will now be "new" fun shaped ones.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, milk, eggs, 1 stick margarine, white sugar and vanilla with electric mixer. Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients and crumble on top of sweet potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turkey and noodles skillet dinner
directions: Prepare egg noodles as label directs, but do not use salt in water; drain.
Meanwhile, cut each mushroom in half or into quarters if large.
Cut celery into 1/2-inch wide slices; cut carrots into bite-size pieces.
Dice onion.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons salad oil, cook celery and onion until tender; remove with slotted spoon to bowl.
In same skillet in 1 more tablespoon hot salad oil, cook mushrooms, stirring frequently until tender and golden.
Remove to bowl with celery and onions.
Meanwhile, in 1 quart saucepan in 1 inch boiling water, heat carrots to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until carrots are tender; drain.

title: pimento-broccoli casserole
directions: Melt cheese in milk and sherry (low heat).
Pour 1/2 in baking dish; layer broccoli, eggs and pimentos.
Add remaining sauce and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are golden, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer chicken and chips in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni salad
directions: Boil chicken in minimum amount of water.
Allow all water to cook out to preserve flavor.
Cook macaroni as package suggests. Stir all ingredients together. Add no water to mushroom soup.
Any or all ingredients after Miracle Whip may be left out.
That gives you the flavors you like.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mint candies
directions: Cook the sugar, water and Karo to 238°.
Add extract.
Stir in powdered sugar. Drop on waxed paper or marble slab in small patties.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cut wieners to bite size.
Heat mustard and jelly together until well mixed.
Add wieners and heat through.
Serve hot from chafing dish.
Spear with toothpicks to eat.

title: yogurt salad dressing or vegetable dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients and chill the sauce.
This is an excellent topping for many vegetarian and Middle Eastern dishes as well as for salad vegetables.

title: parmesan chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture.
Coat both sides.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes. Add ice cubes, 1 or 2 at a time, and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice. Using wire whip or fork, blend Cool Whip.
Whip until smooth. Fold in fruit.
Place fruit on top of pie, if desired.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles or macaroni.
Add onion, soup, tuna and milk. Pour over noodles.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sticky buns
directions: Unroll crescents and divide.
Brush with 3 tablespoons melted butter; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll each section into logs; cut into 4 pieces.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine pie filling, milk and Cool Whip in large bowl.
Add drained pineapple last.
Stir all ingredients until well blended. Refrigerate.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Put into a bowl and add cream of mushroom soup and mixed vegetables.
Stir until blended together well.
Put this mixture into a casserole dish and layer Tater Tots until top of mixture is covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: braised chestnuts and brussels sprouts
directions: Place chestnuts in a heavy saucepan.
Add broth, cornstarch, sherry, salt, pepper and butter to the pan.
Simmer, covered, over very low heat 50 minutes to an hour, until chestnuts are tender. Cook Brussels sprouts separately and combine with chestnuts just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: short bread(english)
directions: Cream butter.
Add flour sifted with cornstarch and sugar and knead until smooth.
Roll out; place on 9-inch baking tin.
Prick all over with a fork.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in 300° oven.

title: heat and hold scrambled eggs
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over low heat.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl; mix until smooth.
Pour mixture into skillet.
As eggs cook, lift outside edges to allow uncooked eggs to flow to outer edge of skillet.
Continue stirring until eggs are cooked, but mixture still has a creamy appearance.
Serve or cover and keep warm until serving time.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Pour batter into a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° until it is golden brown on top. Serve warm or cold with fresh fruit such as strawberries, blueberries, raspberries or peaches and milk.
If cherries are used, remove the seeds and bake the cherries in the cake.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cocoa; add milk, vanilla flavoring and butter.
Cook over medium heat until it begins to become thick, stirring constantly.
Then add beaten egg yolks. Stir and cook 2 minutes.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Add beaten egg whites, sugar and flavoring.
Put meringue on top and bake until brown.

title: karo crazy crunch
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl and combine. Cook remaining ingredients 10 to 15 minutes, stirring all the time (a heavy kettle works better).
When mixture turns a light caramel color, remove from heat and pour over corn mixture.
Coat well. Pour out on a greased cookie sheet.
Spread.
When dry, break in pieces.
Keep in covered container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Pour soup on chicken, then salt and pepper.
Make stuffing.
Use broth instead of just water with the stuffing (makes it more moist).
Spread over chicken, then pour milk over dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook Ro-Tel tomatoes until it starts boiling.
Brown sausage and drain.
Combine Ro-Tel and cheese.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Add sausage.
Serve hot or cold with chips.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine in sauce pan over medium heat.
Add flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Let mixture bubble for 1 minute; slowly stir in milk.
Mixture should start to thicken.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Season with hot sauce.
Makes about 2 cups.
Great over vegetables.

title: tuna shortcake
directions: Blend soup and milk; add tuna, peas and pimiento.
Heat; stir often.
Serve over hot biscuits or toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, then add salt, pepper and garlic. In a 3-quart baking dish, put a layer of browned hamburger, sliced potatoes, kidney beans then repeat; ending with kidney beans. Then add tomato soup on top and smooth. Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: lemon or lime cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, oil, water and lemon rind.
Mix well. Beat eggs.
Add and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (or until done).
Let cake stand in pan about 10 minutes before turning out. (Bake in tube or Bundt pan.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine cooking oil and sugar.
Add eggs, chopped apples, nuts and vanilla.
Stir.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Peel and chop.
Put beets into mixture and boil a few minutes again.
Pack in jars and pour mixture over beets.

title: fantastic potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients except whipping cream.
Whip whipping cream; fold in with other ingredients.
Place in casserole (2-quart).
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Place in bowl and pour 1 cup sugar over.
Set aside.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Grease bottom and sides lightly of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread 1 tube of cookie dough in the bottom of pan.
Combine eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over top of cookie dough in pan.
Crumble other tube of cookie dough on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Refrigerate when cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Place pecans on baking sheet neatly.
Toast at 300° for 8 minutes.

title: monte's strawberry pie
directions: Mix cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, rind and cream.
Cream together until a whipped cream consistency.
Line pie shell with cream cheese mixture and fill with fresh whole ripe strawberries. Cover with strawberry glaze.
Make glaze by mashing strawberries with 1 cup sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Mix with cornstarch and cook until thick and clear.
Pour over pie and refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: turkey dressing and gravy
directions: Put in 325° oven; cover and cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions slowly in shortening.
Add chili powder, salt and soup.
Mix thoroughly and remove from heat.
Add milk.
Pour into greased pan.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° to 425° until biscuits are done and golden brown.

title: spaghetti with shrimp, artichokes and feta cheese
directions: In a skillet, heat the oil and cook the garlic for a few seconds.
Add the tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Let them bubble steadily for 5 minutes.
Set the pan aside.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add the spaghetti; stir until the water returns to a boil.
Let the pasta bubble steadily for 6 to 8 minutes, or until it is tender but still has some bite.
Before you drain the spaghetti, dip a heatproof 2-cup measuring cup into the pot and remove 1 1/2 cups of the cooking liquid.
Drain the pasta; return it to the pot with 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid. Cover the pot; set it aside.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine eggs and milk in bowl. Stir in flour; mix well. Pour into greased 8 inch square pan. Bake for 30 minutes. Yield: 4 to 6 serving.

title: red chile sauce for tamales
directions: Remove stems, and seeds from dried chili peppers.
Place peppers in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Roast in a 350 degree oven for 2 to 5 minutes or until they have a sweet roasted aroma, checking frequently to avoid burning.
Remove from oven; soak peppers in enough hot water to cover about 30 minutes.
Transfer the peppers and 1 to 2 cups of the soaking liquid to a blender container; add garlic, and little salt to taste.
Blend until puree.
(Add liquid, a little at a time while blending until smooth.)
In a large pot add pork broth and pureed chili mixture. Simmer uncovered for 5-10 minutes or until slightly thickened.
If sauce is too thick, stir in additional broth.
Use sauce for tamales.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: doughnut holes
directions: Mix well.
Keep adding liquid until you get consistency desired.
Pour over doughnuts.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Fry hamburger in oleo.
Add water and soup mix, beans, catsup, water, mustard and brown sugar.
Bake at 400° in casserole dish until thick and bubbly, 45 to 55 minutes.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Put meat into food processor to chop.
Mix cream cheese, onion tops, beef and Worcestershire sauce.
Put in a ball or bowl and serve with crackers.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Cook onion in 1 tablespoon butter until soft and tender.
In a bowl, combine egg and half and half. Stir in bread crumbs, onion, salt and parsley. Add meat.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Brown on cookie sheet in oven.
In a skillet, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour, bouillon and coffee. Add water.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add meatballs.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Makes approximately 60 meatballs.
Serve as an appetizer or as a main dish with noodles.

title: honey balls
directions: Wash hands before you start.
Make dough into small balls. Roll dough
in corn flakes.
Put honey ball into a plastic bag.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Put sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan; boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Pour over oatmeal (nuts too, if desired).
Mix and drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Let set until cool and firm.
Put in covered container.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Wash the cabbage, using only the heart and tender parts. Slice the large leaves once and cut all into about 2-inch lengths. Cook cabbage in water or broth for 5 minutes.
Melt butter; add cornstarch paste made with milk.
Cook until thick and add to cabbage.
Continue cooking for another minute and serve hot.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar in bowl.
Pour milk and oil into the flour.
Stir until mixed.
Divide in half.
Roll between waxed paper.
Fit pastry into pan.
Add filling and top crust; bake.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Generously grease bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Reserve 2 to 3 cups dry cake mix for filling.
Combine remaining cake mix in large mixing bowl with melted margarine and 1 egg.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until light golden brown.

title: clover rolls
directions: Heat milk to 120 degrees.
Melt butter in microwave.
Sift together salt and flour.
Combine yeast, warmed water and sugar. Combine milk and butter and add to flour mixture.
Add dissolved yeast mixture and combine.
Knead for 5 minutes, then turn dough onto floured surface.
Spray bowl with vegetable spray and add dough.
Cover bowl with a tea towel and place in a warm spot for 45 minutes or until dough has doubled.
Punch down and turn onto floured surface.
Roll dough until 1/2-inch thick.
Pinch pieces of dough and roll into 1-inch balls.
Spray muffin pan with vegetable spray and place 3 balls into one muffin cup.
Allow dough to rise to rise approximately 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees and bake for 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 24 rolls.

title: brown rice and sausage
directions: Put uncooked rice, water, onion, salt, pepper, coffee and sausage in pot.
Bring to a boil, turn heat down to low after it comes to a boil.
Cook for 30 minutes on low.

title: party dip
directions: In a crock-pot, put soup (undiluted), salsa and cheese (cut in small chunks).
Set on high, stirring occasionally until all is blended.
In a large skillet, brown sausage and ground beef. Drain and add meat to mixture in crock-pot and stir until blended. Can be left on low until you are ready to serve with tortilla chips.

title: wonder frosting
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cream of tartar and water in saucepan. Let come to a full boil and boil 3 minutes.
Add 6 marshmallows until melted.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, breadcrumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, eggs, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Shape into meatballs about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: caramel apple cake dessert
directions: Mix apples and sugar and let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add beaten eggs, salt, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Mix; sift together flour and soda and stir into first mixture.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil together butter, milk, sugar and vanilla for 5 minutes in a heavy saucepan. Remove from heat and add oatmeal, then cook for 1 minute. Add cocoa and coconut. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: "to die for" brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add melted oleo, eggs, flour and vanilla. Beat well. Stir in marshmallows and nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 25 minutes. Do not bake longer!!

title: italian vegetable saute(frugal gourmet p. 191)
directions: Boil the carrots for 5 to 6 minutes, or until tender; remove, and cool.
Add the cauliflower to the same boiling water and cook until barely tender; remove, and cool.
Add the zucchini to the pot, but do not cook long at all.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased skillet. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: hot potato crisps
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/16-inch thick slices.
Toss slices with oil in a large bowl.
Heat oven to 500°.
Spread potato slices in single layers on baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until browned and crisp.
Slide slices onto a serving plate lined with a paper napkin and sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Mix well. Roll out in very small balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° (about 5 minutes).

title: buckeye cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In large mixer bowl, combine cake mix, oil and egg; beat on medium speed until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: pea salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble into small pieces.
Dice green onions. In a large bowl, combine peas, onions, sour cream, Ranch dressing and bacon.
Cover with cheese.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Strain and rinse in cold water.
Butter a baking dish.
Place a layer of macaroni in the bottom of the dish and a layer of cheese over that.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Repeat until the macaroni and cheese are used up.
Beat the egg and add to the milk.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Sprinkle the top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Spread pecans in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Drizzle margarine over pecans.
Drizzle syrup over margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 250° or 300° stirring every 15 minutes.
If pecans stick, add more margarine. Spread on brown paper; sprinkle with salt.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.
Sift flour and soda together.
Mix mashed bananas and flour mixture with egg mixture.
Add nuts and mix.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured tube pan or square pan for 45 minutes.
Do not use electric mixer.

title: candy cane punch
directions: In a saucepan, melt jelly with 2 c. soda.
Chill the jelly mixture and remaining soda just before serving.
Place 6 c. ice cream in a punch bowl.
Gently stir in jelly mixture.
Add remaining soda.
Add remaining ice cream by scoopfuls and garnish with candy canes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and marshmallows together, then add pistachio pudding mix.
Put in refrigerator and chill for about 3 hours.
May add cherries on top if desired.
It stays good in refrigerator for days.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, soup and enchilada sauce.
Layer in large casserole dish the soft tortillas, then meat mixture, then grated cheese.
Then end with layers of cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate to cool.
Roll into balls.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: heavenly manna
directions: Add milk, melted butter, salt and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add yeast.
Beat in 3 1/2 to 4 cups all-purpose flour, beating well after each addition, until you have a stiff but workable batter.
Cover bowl; let rise slowly until double in bulk.
Punch down with wooden spoon for a minute, then scrape into well buttered 9-inch tube pan.
Let rise to top of pan.
Bake in a 375° preheated oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until bread is golden on top and sounds hollow when rapped with knuckles.
Serve warm.
Butter outside of bread for soft crust. (Instead of cutting, break with 2 forks.)

title: sissy's squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread crumbs.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry beets
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir occasionally.
Good with turkey or ham.

title: marinated mushroom bobs
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Place in medium bowl.
Prick tomatoes with fork.
Add to mushrooms along with olives.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Thread mushrooms, tomatoes and olives on toothpicks.
Serve as hors d'oeuvre.
Yield:

title: mushroom stuffed vienna bread
directions: Score bread diagonally in both directions almost to the bottom.
Spread bread open and push in mushrooms and cheese.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Mix oil and sugar well.
Add dry ingredients. Add eggs, pumpkin and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 55 minutes.
Makes 2.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In large skillet, cook pepper, onion and garlic in shortening. Stir in soup, lemon juice, salt, pepper and shrimp.
Heat and serve over fluffy rice.
Serves six.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup softened butter.
Blend on low speed (scraping bowl often) until particles are fine like meal.
Lightly pat mixture in bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown around the edges.

title: pumpkin squares(frozen)
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg. In a chilled bowl, fold pumpkin mixture into ice cream.

title: overnight brunch casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and sausage.
Pour in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuit
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg and milk.
Knead lightly.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and water in stew pan and cook until tender. Add oleo and mushroom soup and let simmer on low heat for 5 minutes; add black pepper to taste.
Serve warm.
Serves 2 or three.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least one hour to blend flavors.

title: ranch flavored oyster crackers
directions: Mix together salad dressing, cooking oil and dill weed.
Pour over oyster crackers.
Let sit in airtight container overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce in pineapple juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add pineapple, pecans and grated rind. Refrigerate before serving.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Blend soup, broth and undrained mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti. In buttered casserole dish, alternate layers of turkey, spaghetti, cheese and soup mixture.
Top with breadcrumbs or Parmesan cheese. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt together 1 stick of oleo and 8 Milky Way bars.
Mix 1 stick oleo, sugar, eggs, flour, soda, buttermilk, vanilla and nuts.
Fold in first melted mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes for loaf cake.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into pizza pan for crust.
Brown sausage and sprinkle over crust.
Add hash browns and grated cheese.
Add salt and pepper to egg and milk mixture and pour over all; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: rick's "wing and rib sauce"
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with wire whisk until smooth. Put into large pot and bring to a very slow rolling boil, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth.
Put aside and let cool several hours.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Sift first five ingredients; set aside.
In a bowl, stir persimmon pulp, evaporated milk, dates, raisins and walnuts.
In a mixing bowl, beat margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
After beating well, alternately add first two mixture groups, mixing well each time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes for cakes. Judge time for small loaf pans.
Use Pam on loaf pans.
Will make 7 little loaves.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix in order listed.
Drop batter from tablespoon into deep fat at 375°.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chocolate cherry spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake as directed; add cinnamon. Fold in 1 can of cherries and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spray Bundt cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
When cool, serve with spoon of cherries.

title: chicken salad hawaiian
directions: Boil and cube chicken.
Add celery, onion, pickles, egg whites, pineapple tidbits, and nuts.
Mix well.
In separate small bowl, mix sour cream, mayonnaise, and enough pineapple juice to make a medium sauce.
Pour over mixture and blend well.
Serve on lettuce leaf or scooped out tomato.
Garnish with paprika.

title: elephant stew
directions: Boil 1 elephant until tender.
Add potatoes, cut in chunks, and add onions, cut up.
Cook until vegetables are done and season to taste.
Feeds 250 or more.

title: norwegian macaroons
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together, then add 1 cup melted butter and last add 1 beaten egg.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet or roll in balls and then flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Melt 2 or 3 cubes of almond bark and drizzle over cookie.
(If almond bark is too thick, add a little oil.)

title: nancy's easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix by hand. Roll into 1-inch balls. Flatten with fork. Bake at 350° approximately 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet until meat loses its red color and onion is light brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Add the vegetable soup and enough water to prevent sticking.
Cover and cook slowly until meat is cooked all through.

title: chocolate peanut candy
directions: Combine 3 packages of chips on bowl. Microwave on Medium for three minutes.
Stir mixture and add peanuts and mix well.
Drop full teaspoon on wax paper. Cool until firm.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown; add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, then add soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with noodles.

title: dijon-glazed chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl; stir well.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and stir in sugar.
Add crumbs (Rice Krispies).
Reserve 1/3 cup to garnish.
Pat crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 12 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix rest of ingredients except topping.
Pour over crust. Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle crumbs over top, then freeze for 4 hours.
Remove from freezer for 20 minutes before serving.

title: shoepeg corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake plain or top with crumbled potato chips or 1/2 package of dry Stove Top stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Let butter or margarine reach room temperature.
Cream with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time (critical!!) and blend each egg in well.
Add flour, 1/3 of amount at a time, blend well with each addition.
Add salt with flour.
Mix in flavorings.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and fat. Mix well. Add vanilla and raisins. Turn into greased baking tin.
Bake in a 350° oven until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: patio lickin' chicken
directions: Brown the chicken lightly.
Mix the other ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place the chicken on top. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and bake another 20 minutes.

title: meat sauce
directions: Mix onion, meat and garlic.
Cook
until browned.
Skim off fat.
Add the rest and 2 cups water.
Cook slowly.
The longer you simmer the better flavor it has.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: royal chicken
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion, mushrooms and chicken pieces; stir-fry until golden brown.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook over medium heat about 35 minutes.
Blend flour, paprika and sour cream.
Stir into liquid in skillet. Bring to a boil and simmer for 3 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Mix together mayonnaise, cream cheese and Ranch mix, then spread over cooled rolls.
Top with chopped veggies and shredded cheese.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute butter and onions until onions are tender.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red wine vinegar marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place ribs, chops, chicken or fish in dish and cover with marinade.
Let stand for 24 hours or at least 3 hours.
Remove meat from liquid and grill over medium-hot coals until nearly done.
Brush on barbecue sauce, turning once or twice.

title: garlic skillet potatoes
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add potatoes, onion, garlic powder with parsley, seasoned salt, seasoned pepper and sugar.
Cook uncovered over medium heat 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender and browned.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon chicken ii
directions: In one dish, place 1/4 cup flour.
