In another dish, mix egg with 2 tablespoons water.
In third dish or on wax paper, combine bread crumbs, garlic and parsley.
Dip chicken pieces in flour, then in the egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Chill about 1 hour. Place butter, oil and lemon juice in frying pan.
Add chicken; saute for about 7 minutes on each side at low heat.
Serve at once.
Easy but so good.
Chicken can be breaded earlier and refrigerated.
Especially good served with a crisp tossed salad and Fettucini Alfredo.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers, onion and pepper.
Will keep in refrigerator for up to 6 months.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook as directed 4 (10 oz) pkgs frozen chopped broccoli. Drain well.
Add cheese mixture. Put in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Top with buttered Rye Bread cubes or croutons. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes or till bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Melt butter on low heat.
Add onions and saute for 5 minutes. Add the mushroom stems, shrimp, salt, pepper and bouillon cubes. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove skillet from heat and stir in cheese, bread crumbs, crabmeat and parsley.
By then, the mixture should be warm enough to mix thoroughly by hand.
Stuff drained mushrooms with stuffing.
Mix equal parts of wine and melted butter.
Pour on top of stuffed mushrooms and heat in oven 15 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first ingredients, sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar. Gradually add onion and oil, then poppy seed.
Refrigerate. Serve over fruit salad. This keeps well in refrigerator.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in deep roasting pan.
Cook 1 hour.
Heat soup in large saucepan.
Cut biscuits in 4 pieces. When soup is hot, drop in biscuits.
When biscuits swell, pour them and soup over chicken (when chicken is done).
Cook for 15 minutes more or until dumplings are brown, if preferred.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients with a fork.
Drop into ungreased muffin tins.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until brown around sides and top.
If using small muffin tins, reduce cooking time to 15 minutes.
Yield: 12 regular or 24 small muffins.

title: mrs. crawford's cherry nut holiday cake
directions: Coat fruit with flour.
Beat the eggs.
Add sugar and rest of ingredients.
Bake in tube pan; line bottom with paper bag and grease all around.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cement pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar and baking powder.
Fold in crushed graham crackers, pecans and vanilla. Pour into a 9-inch pie pan, lightly greased with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with coarsely chopped pecans.

title: salmon loaf with cream sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add salmon. Mix until uniform.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until center is firm in a 350° oven.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Slice and serve with Cream Sauce.

title: toffee bars
directions: Boil butter and sugar 2 minutes.
Pour over pan of whole graham crackers on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pauline's swiss salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in order given in a quart jar and shake thoroughly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form a ball.
Roll cheese ball in chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate and when ready serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Cream butter and 3 tablespoons of sugar together and add pretzels.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: lite vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill and serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: barbara bush's old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cut raisin bread into quarters.
Put 1 layer of bread in dish; sprinkle with sugar mixture and raisins.
Continue to alternate bread and sugar and raisin mixture until dish is full.
Pour milk mixed with vanilla, salt and eggs over all; bake until puffed and lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.
Happy holidays!

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water and vanilla.
After mixing well, add water and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pans for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put 1/2 batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: petit pois frais a la francaise(julia child's green peas, french-style)
directions: Put all ingredients except lettuce into a 3-quart saucepan; top with lettuce.
Cover pan tightly and bring to a boil over moderately high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until peas are tender, stirring once or twice.
Add extra water if pan is dry.
If too liquidy, transfer peas to dish and boil liquid until about 1/3 cup remains.
Pour over peas and serve.

title: cherry nut and date cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Add fruits and pecans.
Grease and flour stemmed pan.
Add mixture and bake at 300° for 2 hours or until done.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Mix chicken and cream cheese.
Roll out rolls and add 1 teaspoon chicken mixture.
Seal rolls.
Bake in buttered pan (using the 1/2 stick of butter) until done.
Heat soup and water; mix well.
Pour over rolls (don't brown rolls).
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: herbed chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken; cool.
Reserve 2 cups of broth.
Remove chicken from bone and tear into bite size pieces.
Place in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Combine soups and 1 cup of broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix margarine and remaining 1 cup of broth.
Stir in stuffing.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: spinach balls(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Cook spinach, drain and squeeze well.
Mix well each ingredient as added to spinach.
Make balls the size of walnuts. Freeze. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Do not thaw first. Serve with sweet and sour or hot mustard, preferably Herlocker's dipping mustard.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/2 stick butter and cornflakes.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick butter.
Pour over 2 cups crushed cornflakes.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered, or until brown.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: It takes about 3 hours total time.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.

title: ham and gravy
directions: Cut ham into chunks.
Place in pressure cooker.
Pour coke over the ham.
Cook for 30 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: hot bacon salad dressing
directions: Cook bacon in frying pan until brown and crispy.
Skim off grease.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Mix well.

title: ternera salteada al jerez(veal scallopini in sherry sauce)
directions: Pound flour, blended with salt, into scallopini using the edge of a saucer.
Saute until golden brown in olive oil.
Separately, saute onions in butter and oil, slowly, until tender, but not brown.
Place scallopini over onions.
Add sherry, chicken consomme, herbs, salt and pepper.
Simmer very gently for about 40 minutes or until scallopini are tender.
Serve topped with chopped almonds and sprinkle oloroso sherry over top at last minute. Serves 6 persons.

title: mabel's egg nog
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Add egg yolks to mixture. Beat whites and fold in last.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: cold cornbread salad
directions: Mix
cornbread,
bell
pepper,	onion, Miracle Whip and black pepper. Chill
overnight.
Just
before serving, stir in chopped tomato and jar of Bac*Os.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Combine oats, flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Add applesauce, milk, brown sugar, oil and egg white; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until deep golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Mix well; add vanilla and lemon flavor. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemonade frosty
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil in a small saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Pour into a small bowl; cover and chill. Place chilled sugar syrup, sorbet and remaining ingredients in a blender. Process until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Cut zucchini in fourths.
Spoon out the seeds and boil on stove.
Open whole down.
Cook, uncovered, until zucchini is fairly soft (not mush).
Take zucchini; place on platter.
Spoon sour cream into zucchini, 1 to 2 teaspoons, then top with Cheddar cheese.
Let sit for 5 minutes so the cheese can melt.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo in frying pan.
Add sugar, egg, dates and nuts. Cook for 5 minutes after mixture starts to bubble.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon into coconut and roll into balls.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend oatmeal in a blender until it's a powder mixture. Grate the Hershey bar and set aside.
Combine flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix flour mixture with sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make golf ball size cookies.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes exactly.
Colored M&M's may be substituted for chocolate chips.

title: perfect barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium size saucepan and bring to boiling, stirring until the sugar dissolves.
Simmer. Makes about 3 cups.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well.
Add crackers last and mix again.
Make sure crackers are soft before putting in the mix.
Make small balls in loaf pan.
Then put a spoon of cream of mushroom soup on each ball.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together; save egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° until firm (about 1 hour).
Beat egg whites and add 2 tablespoons sugar for each egg white.
Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake until brown.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Blend all ingredients in large container.
Freeze at least 2 days.
Serve with Sprite, 7-Up or ginger ale.
Great for big parties!

title: carrots in onion sauce
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until limp.
Stir in carrots, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently until sauce coats the carrots and is slightly thickened.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add carrots.
Add flour, a little at a time, then the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into two round pans, greased and floured.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring; mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours, or until done.

title: on top of stove casserole - mine
directions: Mix all ingredients.
I made this on the farm when I didn't know what to make in a hurry!

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion; cook until yellow and tender.
Add cheese whip.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Add broccoli to cheese mixture.
Add egg; stir through the mixture.
Add 2 fistfuls of saltine crackers to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Mix together and put in pie crust.
Top with reserved sour cream mixture.
Top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese and chopped olives.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve in wedges.
(Chicken better cooked in onions and bay leaf.)

title: scallop and spaghetti casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, combine cooked scallops, spaghetti, sherry and pimiento.
Mix white sauce as directed on package and mix together with above ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: honolulu dip
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Serve in small bowls with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Pour sugar over first mixture and let stand until set, one hour.
Mix three packages of gelatin with 3 1/2 cups boiling water.
Let almost jell, then add to other mixture.
Chill.
Let set.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and trim broccoli.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Add bacon, green onions, raisins and water chestnuts. In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Add dressing to broccoli mixture and toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 10 people.

title: brownie pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl, cream shortening, butter, and sugar with electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
In a separate bowl, sift 3 cups of flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add sifted ingredients and milk to creamed mixture alternating each. Beginning and ending with sifted mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Combine pecans with 2 tablespoons of flour to prevent pecans from settling to the bottom.
Fold pecans into batter. Bake in a well greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours or until a wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Turn out of pan and top with Mel's chocolate topping.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a dark roux as follows:
In large skillet, stir oil and flour over medium heat until dark brown.
Stir constantly or it will burn and be bitter.
Add onions and garlic and cook until soft; do not brown.
Add chicken stock to skillet; stir and transfer to a large pot, then add the next 5 ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours, adding Old Bay seafood seasoning every 30 minutes. Taste after a couple of tablespoons since some seasoning may be too hot for your taste.
Add the remainder of ingredients.
Cook another 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink and crabs are red. Serve over rice and add file to taste.
Serves about 8 and can be frozen.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over the mixture.
Melt 2 sticks oleo and pour over cake.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, mayo, cheese and green onions. Mix well. Put in a pan. Then add your Fritos. Either use chili cheese or plain Fritos. Mix all together. Then serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sear meat.
Saute onions (and fresh mushrooms if you use them).
Add remaining ingredients and cook in crock-pot or on top of stove slowly for 2 to 4 hours.

title: pear pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oleo and eggs.
Grease a baking dish.
Place pared and sliced pears on bottom, then add bread.
Pour mixture of sugar, flour, oleo and eggs over bread.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: chesapeake bay crab cakes
directions: Mix together, adding crab last. Form into 4 patties. Fry in oil until golden.

title: fried pumpkin
directions: Remove the hard core in the center of each bloom.
Dip into thin batter. Fry in hot fat or oil until crisp and brown. Serve right away.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread thaw overnight.
Roll out and put damp dish towel over for 5 minutes.
Roll again into rectangle.
Leave an edge. Beat 1 egg and brush over bread.
Layer ham, cheese, pepperoni and salami.
Beat another egg and pour over.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Mix brown sugar, water and salt together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes.
Add flavoring.
Mix and pour over pancakes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add alternately with the buttermilk, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Combine orange slices, dates, coconut and nuts.
Coat with the flour. Add to batter.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza burgers(open faced burgers)
directions: Spread buns or bread open faced on broiler pan.
Brown meat and add the pizza sauce.
Mix well and simmer until done but still moist.
Cover buns with meat mixture.
Shake Parmesan cheese evenly over all burgers.
Place under broiler for abut 5 minutes or until bubbling.

title: nok qui vi(texas style)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in a 4-quart stock pot until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients, except jalapeno peppers.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer gently for 45 minutes.
For hotter stew, add peppers when stock comes to a boil.
Serve hot with fry bread and honey.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: anise oat buns
directions: Bring milk to boiling point and pour it over the oats, rye flour, crushed anise, salt and honey in a large bowl.
Mix together.
Cover the mixture with a clean towel or plastic wrap and let it cool to 98.6° C. (body temperature).
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 to 1/2 cup lukewarm water and add to the mixture.
Work in enough white flour to make dough solid enough to shape into buns.
This dough is very sticky and cannot be kneaded.
It needs no first rising.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Bake in a small casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot with French or Italian bread.

title: monterey jack-crab muffins
directions: Toast the English muffins.
Mix the crab, mayonnaise and pepper together; spread on English muffins.
Cover each muffin with a slice of Monterey Jack and brown for a few minutes under the broiler.

title: applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs and applesauce. Mix well. Add flour and spices. Mix well. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoon fulls. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon cold water.
Mix all together.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: walnut or hickory pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add walnuts and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until center is firm, approximately 45 minutes.

title: lazy lasagna for 2
directions: Warm the Spaghetti Sauce; stir in Cottage Cheese and Mozzarella.
Fold in Noodles.
Pour into two greased 2-cup casseroles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan Cheese.
Bake uncovered at 374 for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix peas, mushrooms, water chestnuts and soup together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruitcake squares
directions: Pour melted oleo in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle evenly with wafer crumbs.
Arrange cherries, pineapple, dates and pecans evenly over the crumbs.
Press down gently.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: fudge scotch ring
directions: Melt chocolate	and
butterscotch
morsels
with Borden sweetened milk in
top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir
occasionally	until
morsels	melt
and
mixture begins to thicken.	Remove	from
heat.
Add
chopped nuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Butter
round
cake pan or round casserole dish.
Put	walnut	halves around it.
Put mixture on top of nuts and add nut halves to the top of that.

title: one dish pork chop dinner
directions: Coat pork chops in flour.
In large Dutch oven, melt butter; brown chops.
Set aside.
Stir excess flour into pan.
Whisk in 1 1/2 cups apple juice.
Return chops to pot.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add potatoes, onions, carrots and 1/2 cup apple juice.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Top with cabbage.
Cover and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours longer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brush mushroom caps with oil and place them on a buttered cookie sheet.
In a mixing bowl, combine crab meat, egg, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and 1/4 cup of bread crumbs.
Fill each cap with mixture.
Combine 1/4 cup bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over the top of mushrooms.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until thick; add jello. Cool, then add berries.
Pour into pie crust.

title: school days no bake cookies(yields 4 to 5 dozen)
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt in a saucepan. Cook to softball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper. Cool.

title: monkey bread #1
directions: Roll each biscuit in cinnamon; place in Bundt pan that has been oiled.
Melt butter and mix with cinnamon and sugar left. Pour over the pieces of biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 22 minutes. Turn out.
Serve hot.
Just pull apart.

title: sheryl's pork roast
directions: Boil roast on low heat for 2 hours with red pepper.
Take up and put in casserole bowl.
Cut up tomatoes, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Arrange over roast.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve while hot.

title: speedy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and margarine with electric mixer.
Add egg and beat well.
Add soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add flour, oats and nuts; mix well with wooden spoon.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and allow to cool slightly on baking sheet.
Then remove with pancake turner and place cookies on wire cooling rack.

title: fruit squares
directions: First, cut margarine into flour, sugar and baking powder. Then beat eggs with vanilla.
Pour egg into crumb mixture. Continue to mix until mixture is all crumbs.
Then press 1/2 of crumbs into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling and sprinkle the rest of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When cool, cut into squares.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, egg, onion, and salt.
Form into about 100 small meatballs and arrange in electric skillet.
Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice.
Pour over meatballs and simmer for one hour.
Serve in heated dish.

title: floyd's salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and beat until creamy.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Fry chopped beef in hot oil about 10 minutes or until slightly brown.
Add garlic, onion, mushrooms and parsley; saute for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add salt, pepper and tomatoes; simmer 1 hour or until sauce is of thick consistency.
Cook spaghetti 20 minutes in 5 quarts of rapidly boiling salted water.
Drain.
Place on serving dish; add hot sauce; sprinkle with grated Pecorino cheese.
Any type of macaroni nay be served with this meat sauce. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: balsamic salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shake well or blend in mixer. Keeps well.

title: warm shrimp dip
directions: Mix first five ingredients with a few gurgles of sherry and heat in fondue pot until melted and smooth.
Add shrimp.
Thicken with cornstarch until desired dipping consistency.
Serve with Bugles or chips.

title: tea scones
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add butter bits and rub in.
Add currants.
Beat egg and add milk.
Make a well in center of flour mixture; add egg/milk mixture.
Mix until flour is incorporated.
Turn out on floured board.
Roll out into a 1-inch thick circle.
(If desired, brush with lightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with coarse sugar.)
Cut dough into 8 to 10 triangles.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: anise cookies (or butter cookies)
directions: *With this recipe you can
make
a butter cookie as is, or you can make the anise
cookies.
Use
about
1 to 2 tablespoons of anise seed and cut out vanilla and almond extract.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into small balls and brown in oil.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer, covered, about 45 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: grilled chicken with a peach and green chili sauce
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together the cumin, the orange juice, the oil and 1 tablespoon of the chili powder.
Arrange the chicken in a large shallow baking dish and pour the marinade over it, turning the chicken to coat it well.
Let the chicken marinate, covered and chilled, for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: sweet smells
directions: Combine ingredients in a potpourri burner or pot on top of stove, adding water as needed.

title: apple pecan muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Add next 2 ingredients. In another bowl, combine the next 7 ingredients.
Add to flour mixture.
Spoon into 12 paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion and pepper in oil over medium heat until tender. Stir in pineapple juice, brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and salt. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes to blend flavors.
In cup, stir cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water until smooth.
Gradually add cornstarch mixture to pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until boiling.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Cool.

title: homemade "pizza"
directions: Top each slice of bread with ketchup and a slice or 2 of American cheese.
Toast in toaster oven or heat under broiler until cheese melts. Adventurous children can use spaghetti sauce and sliced
or shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Kids like to make this themselves.

title: zucchini omelet(for one person.)
directions: Cut zucchini in half.
Boil for 10 minutes or until done.
In a small bowl, beat egg with milk.
Add parsley and seasonings. Beat again.
Add cooked zucchini.
Cook in a nonstick skillet over moderate heat until almost done.
Top with cheese.
Fold over.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix corn and Bisquick; put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes, or until browned.

title: black sour milk cake
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over 2 cups sugar, shortening and cocoa.
Combine soda, flour and salt.
(Do not sift flour.)
Add flour mixture to cocoa mixture.
Beat eggs and add sour milk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
(Do not overbeat.)
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Cake will keep fresh and moist in covered pan for days.
Rich enough without frosting.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together, then pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt margarine and caramels on low heat; mix well.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Sprinkle nutmeats and chocolate chips over baked cake; pour caramel mixture over all.
Pour remaining batter over caramels. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water immediately. Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple including juice.
Chill approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Mix 3 cups Cool Whip into gelatin mixture.
Cut or break angel food cake into small pieces.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer pieces of cake and then layer of gelatin until all cake is used.
Chill.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with cherries.

title: "can" do chicken
directions: Mix in skillet (not onion rings) and simmer about 10 minutes. Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix La Creme, sour cream and sugar.
Fold in berries and cherries.

title: great bean seasoning
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a jar or plastic bag and seal tightly.
I use 3 tablespoons for every 3 cups of dried beans.

We liked the 15 bean package of beans so well that I mixed up my own variety of beans and it follows that I had to mix up my own recipe for the seasoning. Just start with this recipe and do your own taste test.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Dissolve 1 package raspberry jello in 2 cups hot water.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan and chill until set.
Heat cream and sugar; dissolve unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Combine with cream. Add vanilla, cream cheese and nuts.
Pour over set jello.
Set again.
Dissolve other raspberry jello in 1 cup hot water.
Stir in blueberries and juice.
Pour over cheese layer and chill.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Combine 1 package jello and 1 cup boiling water.
When jello is dissolved, add peach syrup and sliced peaches.
Pour into square dish or mold and set in refrigerator until firm.
Pour 1 cup boiling water, 1 package jello and cream cheese cubes in blender.
Blend on low speed until cheese is mixed.
Add milk and blend until mixed.
Pour cream cheese-jello mix on top of firm peach layer and chill until firm.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in other ingredients. Put in 1-quart mold.
Chill.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add egg and dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Add molasses last.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: choco-nut caramel bars
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water milk chocolate morsels and vegetable shortening.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Pour 1/2 of melted chocolate into an 8-inch foil-lined square pan; spread evenly.
Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes).
Return remaining chocolate mixture to low heat.
Combine over boiling water the caramels, butter and water.
Stir until caramels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts until well blended.
Pour into chocolate-lined pan.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate until tacky, about 15 minutes.

title: hershey's kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend flour, soda and salt.
Add butter, peanut butter and sugar (cream these together first).
Add sugar and brown sugar, then egg and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.
When removed from oven, immediately place one Hershey's Kiss in middle of each cookie.
Press down slightly. Place back in oven for 3 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: angel food punch bowl cake
directions: Put half of the cake pieces in a punch bowl.
Cover with half of pineapple, half of cherry pie filling, half of prepared vanilla pudding and half of Cool Whip.
Repeat sequence.
Very tasty and a quick dessert.
Enjoy.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Put in heavy sauce pan. Stir over medium heat until chocolate and marshmallows melt completely and mixture thickens. Serve over ice cream.

title: chicken tikka
directions: Mix yogurt with chili powder, ginger, garlic, garam masala, salt and red food coloring.
Pour over chicken pieces and mix well.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix well.
Line the broiler pan with baking foil.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Brush with oil and broil then for 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Brush with oil occasionally and continue cooking until chicken is tender. Serve with wedges of lemon and a crisp lettuce salad.

title: bake-on-cake icing
directions: Spread on hot cake and return to oven or place under broiler until it bubbles.
Take out and cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine all ingredients except last two in large bowl.
Put in large casserole dish.
Bake.
Sprinkle topping on.

title: turkey with peppers
directions: In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Add turkey and coat in mixture.
In large skillet, heat oil and cook garlic and turkey mixture over high heat, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Stir in peppers and onions. Cook over medium-high, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Beat eggs and lemon juice.
Put in saucepan.
Cook slow until thickened.
Let cool.
Pour over Cool Whip and cream cheese. Chill the Orange-Pineapple Salad.

title: lowfat broccoli cheese soup
directions: Combine hash browns, onions, and chicken broth in a soup pot. Cook until hash browns are tender.
Puree in a blender or food processor.
Return to soup pot and add the evaporated milk, broccoli, lemon pepper seasoning, Velveeta, and Parmesan.
Stir continuously until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.
Less than 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Wash and chop broccoli.
Cook 5 minutes in boiling salt water. Melt butter in a 2 or 3-quart pan.
Add flour, stirring to keep smooth.
Add broth to butter/flour mixture, stirring
constantly to deep smooth.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add broccoli to soup base and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add seasonings, cheese, nutmeg and milk.
Stir until all ingredients are well blended.

title: oven lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, brown meat, onion and garlic; drain.

Return mix to skillet; stir in spaghetti sauce and water. In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1/3 of sauce mixture, half of uncooked lasagna noodles, 1/2 of cottage cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Cover and bake 1 hour. Uncover; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.
Freeze leftovers.

title: roast potatoes with herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss potatoes with herbs and enough olive oil to lightly coat (about 3 to 4 tablespoons).
Place potatoes in a large roasting pan.
Roast in a preheated oven; shake occasionally so that all sides are evenly browned.
Cook until fork-tender (about 40 minutes); season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in Pet milk in a double boiler. Add the remaining ingredients. Put in a container lined with aluminum foil and store in the refrigerator. Chill well before slicing.

title: ground beef and mushroom casserole
directions: Brown beef; add uncooked Rice-A-Roni.
Cook until rice mixture is light brown.
Add 2 cups hot water and the Rice-A-Roni seasoning packet.
Stir well; let simmer 10 minutes.
Add sauteed onions and pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, mushrooms and soup.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in large greased casserole, uncovered.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, spread raw rice on bottom of dish.
Stir 1 cup of water into the soup mix.
Pour soup mix over rice.
Brown the pork chops; place on top of soup and rice.
Pour the soup on top of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Pour half and half milk into large mixing bowl.
Add pie filling and instant coffee.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm (about 6 hours).
Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes to soften.
Top with sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Cook all together until it forms a hard ball in water.
Take off fire and add pecans.
Beat until thickens.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots in strips or slice.
Cook in small amount of water until barely tender.
Drain and cool.
Slice onion thin and cut green pepper into strips.
Combine with carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Chill for 3 hours or overnight.

title: carol's banana split
directions: Make crust:
Place in bottom of pan.
Beat at high speed the powdered sugar, eggs and soft margarine for 12 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas over filling; sprinkle pineapple (drained well) over bananas.
Spread half Cool Whip over pineapple; slice 2 or 3 more bananas over pineapple.
Spread remaining Cool Whip.
Top with crushed pecans and cherries. Refrigerate.

title: critters-n-creme
directions: Bake cookies according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Place about 1/4 cup ice cream between 2 cookies and gently press together.
Serve immediately or wrap in aluminum foil and freeze.
Makes 18 ice cream sandwiches.

title: do ahead chicken rice bake
directions: Take the
boned,
skinned and flattened chicken breasts and cut each in
half.
Mix
rice, celery, green pepper, parsley, pimento,
seasonings
and
sour cream together.
Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly
with
salt
and
pepper.
Place
1/2 tablespoon cold butter
and
tablespoons
rice
mixture
in center of each chicken
breast
half.
Fold
each breast over filling in envelope
fashion, folded narrow way first and then the
long way.
Fasten
with toothpicks.
Beat egg and cream. Roll
folded breasts in flour, then in egg-cream mixture, then in
crumbs. Allow
to
stand 10 minutes before frying in deep hot fat (360°) for 15 minutes.
Remove toothpicks.
Serve with Quick Sour Cream Sauce (see recipe below).
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and cook until done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Separate egg. Measure milk, drop yolk and beat together. Add liquid to dry. Beat egg white.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash squash.
Mix with carrots, onions, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Butter casserole dish; sprinkle layer of crumbs in bottom.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with crumbs.
Dot generously with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and put in casserole dish. Combine all other ingredients, except onion rings, and pour over broccoli.
Top with onion rings.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cioppino
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces. Scrub and soak mussels/clams in water and corn meal for about 1 hour.
Combine oil, onion, pepper, celery and garlic in 4-quart casserole.
Cook, uncovered, on high 5 minutes until soft.
Mash and add tomato, basil, bay leaf, salt and pepper. Cook, covered, for 15 minutes. Add fish, shrimp and scallops.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Layer clams/mussels on top and cook, covered, for 10 minutes. Serve over hot pasta, garnished with parsley sprigs.

title: red rice
directions: Brown sausage and remove.
Saute onions and bell pepper until onions transparent.
Add sausage and remainder of ingredients. Stir and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain 1 pound green beans.
Marinate in 1/4 cup Italian dressing 1 or 2 hours or overnight.
Mix with potatoes, onion and parsley.
Then blend mayonnaise, sour cream and salt.
Fold about 2/3 of mixture into green beans and potatoes.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with remaining sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs, then paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Add chicken soup and sour cream. Pour into dish.
Melt butter and pour over crushed Ritz crackers. Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Soak bread in water 2 to 3 minutes.
Squeeze out moisture. Combine soaked bread with remaining ingredients and mix well. Form into balls.
Brown slowly in 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add to Italian Red Gravy sauce and cook 1 hour.

title: nut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add brown sugar.
Then add the sour milk in which soda has been dissolved.
Sift baking powder with flour.
Add to other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add nut meats.
Bake in moderate oven from 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Line greased 9 X 9 casserole with small package of Fritos.
Mix chilies, milk, soup and onion.
Pour over Fritos and top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in 4 eggs, add pineapple and 1/2 cup juice.
Stir in bread cubes and bake in greased casserole at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.
Enjoy with ham and chicken dishes.

title: muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine oat bran cereal, nuts, raisins and baking powder. Stir in brown sugar.
Mix milk, egg whites and oil together and blend in with oat bran mix.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes. Makes 12.

title: preacher's rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add rice.
Boil rapidly; add salt. Boil for approximately 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain rice and rinse with warm water.
Makes approximately 5 cups of cooked rice. Great for a crowd.

title: dishpan cookies(oatmeal)
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes (depending on your oven's heat).
This cookie dough may be refrigerated and baked at your convenience.
This recipe is actually 1/2 of the original recipe.
This batch makes 6 dozen or more cookies.

title: sweet potato crust
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Add baking powder and salt; sift again.
Work in mashed sweet potatoes, melted butter and egg. Roll 1/4-inch thick and use as cover for chicken or meat deep dish pie.
Yields pastry for 1 (9-inch) crust.

title: swedish yule crispy(cookies)
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour mixture. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into cinnamon and nut mixture. Flatten with a small glass (orange juice size).
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes (on ungreased cookie sheets).
Makes 4 dozen.

title: steak and browned rice
directions: Salt, pepper and flour steaks.
Brown on both sides and cut into bite size pieces.
Brown rice and onion in oleo.
Add soup, mushrooms and steak.
Pour into baking dish and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: muffin tin breakfast
directions: Line muffin tins with a slice of ham about the thickness of a slice of bologna.
Break an egg onto each ham slice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until egg is firm.
Remove with spatula and serve immediately.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: almond crisp
directions: In a deep saucepan, combine butter and sugar. Cook at medium-low heat, stirring constantly, to 210° on candy thermometer. Add almonds. Continue to cook and stir until temperature reaches 300°. Pour quickly onto a lightly buttered cookie sheet. Work fast and spread the mixture very thin. Spread half of the chocolate chips over the candy. As it melts, spread evenly over all. Sprinkle half the pecan meal evenly over the chocolate. When cool, carefully turn candy over onto counter. Melt the remaining chocolate chips in the top of a double boiler and spread evenly. Quickly add the remaining pecan meal. When cold and set, break into pieces.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring all ingredients, except popcorn, together in saucepan; boil for 5 minutes. Pop 2 gallons popcorn and empty onto cookie sheet. Pour syrup over popcorn and stir.
Place in 350° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Melt sugar in water and Karo.
Add peanuts and cook until mixture forms a good thread (240°).

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water to dissolve jello.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well and let congeal.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of jello.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: cheezy baked tomatoes
directions: Remove top of tomato, approximately 1/4-inch, and scoop out bulk pulp.
Do not scrape to the outer wall; leave some tomato intact.
Cut very thin slice from bottom of tomato (1/16th-inch) to allow each tomato to sit on baking pan and not roll.
Divide Parmesan cheese and place in each tomato; repeat with shredded cheese.
Reserve small amount of bacon drippings and season each tomato before adding crumbled bacon to each.
Bake in oven or on grill at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until tomato skin begins to wrinkle.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed.
Bake in 2 round cake pans.
When cool slice in middle of both layers.

title: komle (potato dumpling)(international dish)
directions: Dice pork. Mix all ingredients except pork. Shape into balls with hands. Put pieces of pork in center of dumplings. Add enough flour to keep them from sticking. Drop into boiling broth. Cover and boil 1 hour. Stir occasionally to prevent dumplings from sticking to bottom of kettle. Remove from broth as soon as done. Serve hot with butter. Serves 6.

title: italian style spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in oil until onion is transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover, simmer 45 to 50 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat butter, egg yolks, almond extract, coconut and sugar. Alternately add flour and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Gently fold in.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° until done when tested.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour in large skillet.
Add milk, eggs, vanilla and butter.
Cook until thick.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Make cake with rest of ingredients, stirring in nuts after blending.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes, then remove cake to rack to finish cooling.
May dust with powdered sugar.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in kidney beans, French dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add lettuce, green onions and 1 1/2 cups cheese; toss lightly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serve with crisp tortillas, if desired.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: teal chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
If wings are used, it is too hard to skin them. Wash and drain.
Prepare crumb mixture from the flour, Italian bread crumbs and corn flake crumbs in pot or bowl.
Pour evaporated milk into bowl.
Dip pieces of chicken in milk, then turn them over in crumbs.
Place in large baking pan.
Put into a 425° oven for 1/2 hour or until light tan.
In the last half, put on top shelf to brown.
Do not burn.
Take chicken out.

title: frosty apple health drink
directions: Add all ingredients in a large bowl and beat until frothy. Pour into a chilled punch bowl.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg to taste. Serves 25.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Put a chicken breast between a piece of plastic wrap and pound with a meat mallet or edge of a saucer until it is about 1/4-inch thick.
Do this to all chicken breasts.

title: distinctively different slaw
directions: Break Ramen noodles into small pieces. Set seasoning packet aside. In a large bowl, stir together broken Ramen noodles, cabbage with carrots, almonds, green onions and sunflower seeds; set aside.
In a screw-top jar, combine salad oil, sugar, white vinegar and seasoning packet from noodles.
Cover and shake to dissolve sugar. Pour over cabbage mixture; toss to coat.
Serve immediately. (Or cover and chill in the refrigerator for up to 4 hours.) Makes 10 to 12 side dish servings.

title: salmon fettucini
directions: Saute red peppers, zucchini and garlic in butter.
Remove from pan.
Add half and half to pan; heat.
Combine with sauteed vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly.

title: never fail crust
directions: Shake in bowl: flour, shortening and salt. In a small bowl, combine: egg and vinegar. Beat with a fork, then add water. Pour in dry mixture and mix with hands.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat milk, butter, flour and salt just until smooth.
Mix in eggs, one at a time, but do not over-beat.
(Batter should be no heavier than whipping cream.)
Butter and flour muffin pans.
Fill each tin no more than 3/4 full.
Bake immediately for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and continue baking for 20 more minutes.
DO NOT OPEN OVEN!!
Test one popover for doneness by removing it and checking to see if sidewalls are firm.
If popovers are not cooked completely, they will collapse.

title: apple cheese turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and salt.
With a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in 1 1/2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese and butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle with water.
Stir with a fork until dough clings together.
Shape into a ball.
With a floured rolling pin, roll dough on a lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Using the tip of a sharp knife, cut around a 6 1/2-inch saucer to form 6 circles.
Reserve pastry scraps.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken fingers
directions: Cut each breast half into 4 strips.
Combine next five ingredients.
Combine egg and buttermilk.
Dip chicken into egg mixture and then dredge in flour mixture. Pour margarine into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Drain.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat the whites of the eggs to soft peaks.
Add the yolks of the eggs and beat again.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla in that order slowly and beat well.
Sprinkle with nutmeg to taste.
Makes about 15 servings.

title: southwest style chicken
directions: Take chicken off bones.
Mix all ingredients except half of grated cheese.
Dip shells in broth and line a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer mixture, then add more shells and more mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in oven at 425° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf with rice
directions: Mix above ingredients
except 1/2 cup beef broth (I use bouillon cubes).
Place mixture in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You
may use 1/2 cup broth as needed if meat becomes too dry.

title: crunchy potato-beef casserole
directions: Saut the onion and green pepper in a skillet that has been coated with no-stick cooking spray.
When the vegetables are tender, add the ground round, the tomato sauce and the onion soup mix.
Place the mixture in a baking dish that has been coated with no-stick cooking spray.
Top the meat mixture with the shredded potatoes.
Lightly spray the potatoes with no-stick cooking spray. Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.
Makes 4 servings, 4 fat grams per serving.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in the blender container; mix together.
Just prior to pouring into an unbaked crust, add the cup of nut meats and spin to distribute in filling.
It is easy to pour this filling when the unbaked shell has been placed in or near the oven, because it makes a large pie and is easily spilled when moved.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, until it tests done.

title: 48 hour potato salad
directions: Cook
potatoes	until fork-tender, peel and cube.
Dice celery.
Dice red onions.
In a large container you can cover, layer
in the following manner:
potatoes, enough diced celery to cover
potatoes,
enough diced red onions to cover, enough cottage cheese
to cover.	Spread mayo, making sure you cover entire salad
at least 1/2-inch.
Cover and leave alone for 24 hours. Stir
and leave another 8 to 10 hours.
Stir again and serve. Great for parties as can be fixed ahead of time.
Will keep up to 10 days.

title: garlic grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken; mix well.
Add chicken and marinate 1 to 2 hours or longer.
Remove chicken from marinade and grill until done.
Boil marinade well.
Good served over rice or noodles.
(I often double marinade.)

title: shredded brussels sprouts with lemon
directions: Chop the onion.
Mince the garlic.
Shred Brussels sprouts by finely slicing with a knife.
Grate 1 teaspoon of yellow zest from lemon and squeeze 3 tablespoons juice.
In a large frying pan over medium-high heat, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Add the Brussels sprouts, reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring occasionally, until sprouts are just tender, about 5 minutes for frozen or 15 minutes for fresh.
Add the lemon zest and juice, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and stir in the Parmesan cheese. Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Place in stockpot and cover with water.
Cook on medium heat until tender.
Do not salt.
Do not drain.
Add soups, stirring until blended.
Cube cheese and add. Stir until melted.
Add Pet milk and stir.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In double boiler heat chocolate and butter.
Stir in sugar and milk.
Stir until it thickens.
Add vanilla.

title: manicotti
directions: Boil noodles as directions say.
Mix in bowl the cheeses and oregano.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Put shells in 11 x 9 x 2-inch pan (glass).
Cover with Prego.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until noodles and cheese are done.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Heat sugar and corn syrup to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over popcorn and stir.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix all together and heat in crock-pot or place in oven at 400° for 1 hour.
Add more tomato juice if desired.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: bread
directions: Work into ball.
Let rise (double).
Knead down again (let raise double).
Knead and put into bread pans.
Pierce with fork. Let raise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 400° for 30 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.
Wipe with butter when still warm from oven.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Chop vegetables very fine; mix and sprinkle with salt.
Put in colander and catch drippings.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add enough tomato juice to make at least 1 1/2 cups.
Bring liquid to a boil and add envelope of plain gelatin.
Cool (I place pot in cold water).
Add mayonnaise and chopped vegetables.
Chill 24 hours before using.
Spread bread lightly with butter before spreading sandwiches.

title: brown sugar divinity
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir together the sugars, water, corn syrup and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, continue boiling gently until 262° on candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites in large bowl until soft peaks.
Beating constantly at high speed, pour hot syrup over egg whites.
Beat in vanilla.
Beat until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Can pour into lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2 pan..
Cut into squares.

title: ham casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, mushrooms and onion.
Add ham, uncooked macaroni, pimiento and dash pepper.
Mix well.
Bake covered in a 375° oven about 50 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Uncover; sprinkle cheese on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: greek bread*
directions: Split French bread down the center lengthwise.
Mix together mayonnaise, oleo, cheese, garlic powder, green onions and olives. Spread over the French bread.
Bake at 325° until cheese is melted and bubbly, about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: easy rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease (Pam spray) and flour a 10-inch tube or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all cake ingredients together.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool.
Invert on a serving plate.
Prick top.
Drizzle and smooth with Rum Glaze (follows) evenly over top and sides.
Allow cake to absorb glaze.
Repeat until the glaze is used up.

title: sauce for broccoli(substitute for cheese sauce)
directions: Combine water and cornstarch, making a smooth paste. Add other ingredients. Simmer until moderately thick.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and brown and granulated sugars in a large bowl. Beat in vanilla and eggs. Sift remaining dry ingredients together. Add to sugar-egg mixture, blending well. Stir in 1/2 cup candies. Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet; decorate tops with remaining candies. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sole poached with tomatoes, artichokes and mushrooms
directions: In heavy saucepan or skillet, melt butter (or substitute chicken broth); cook mushrooms and garlic over medium-high heat, shaking pan or stirring until mushrooms are tender.
Add tomatoes, basil and thyme, bring to a simmer for 3 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer until fish is opaque.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
makes 4 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown hamburger with liver and diced onion and pepper.
Drain and season to taste.
Mix with rice and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and canned milk.
Add baking soda, baking powder, cocoa and flour.
Stir in zucchini.
Spread in greased, floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix 5 tablespoons sugar with cinnamon, then mix with apples. Mix remaining ingredients together.
In tube pan, layer batter, apples, batter, apples and batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: amish cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add eggs, pineapple, vanilla and nuts.
Stir all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make grapefruit size balls.
Roll between waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 5 hours or more.
Bake at lowest setting on oven.
Baste with 1/4 cup water and 1/4 cup liquid smoke.
Bake for 4 to 5 hours.
Cool; cut into strips.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter, salt and nutmeg.
Add milk and beaten eggs. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 7 minutes or at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Pat biscuits to desired size.
Spread spaghetti sauce on each biscuit.
Top with other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream flour, butter and powdered sugar; spread in greased pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Yields 6 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown sausage and onions together.
Into this add potatoes and water.
Cook until potatoes are done (about 20 minutes).
Add corn and milk.
Heat but not boil.

title: dewey lemon salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water and combine soda and pineapple juice with jello.
Let thicken slightly.
Add marshmallows, bananas and pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set until solid.
Whip Dream Whip and add lemon pie filling.
Put on top of jello. Refrigerate.

title: chocolatetown special cake
directions: Stir together cocoa and boiling water until smooth; set aside. Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla in large bowl until fluffy. Add eggs; beat well.

title: onion cake
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon; discard drippings.
In same skillet, cook onion in oleo until tender; cool.
In mixing bowl, combine sour cream, flour and salt.
Add eggs; stir in bacon and onion; set aside.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Pat dough into bottom and 1-inch up sides of 9-inch square greased pan, stretching as needed.
Pinch edges together to seal.
Pour mixture over dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Yields 16.

title: pop-in-a-pan frozen peach pie
directions: Scald, peel and slice peaches.
Measure 4 quarts.
Dissolve ascorbic acid in water.
Add peaches.
Drain.
Combine peaches with other ingredients.
Line 4 (8-inch) pie pans with heavy-duty foil, letting it extend about 5 inches beyond rim.
Divide filling in pans.
Fold foil over loosely; freeze until firm.
Cover tightly with foil; remove from pan and return to freezer.
May be stored for 6 months.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; add coconut.
Mix and add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add oatmeal and candy pieces.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar and milk. Pour half of the batter into greased and floured bundt pan. Sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar. (Mix sugar and cinnamon in amounts that suit you.) Pour in remaining batter. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool. Mix together powdered sugar and milk. Pour over cooled cake.

title: football fans' frijole dip(spicy bean dip)
directions: Save liquid from jar of commercial dill pickles.
Add fresh peas, snapped beans, carrot sticks, cauliflower flowerets, cucumber slices, etc.
Chill and serve.

title: ceviche
directions: Rinse shrimp and place in large bowl.
Drain, reserving liquid. Add clams to bowl.
Add minced cucumber, minced onion, cilantro, 1/4 cup chopped tomatoes, chopped carrots and lime juice from limes.
Add reserved liquid from clams.
Add jalapenos with seeds removed unless you like it hot.
Mix well.
Add garlic salt for flavor.
Add avocados last.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Cream ingredients and spoon over first mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour melted margarine over pan bottom.
Mix ingredients and pour into baking pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon (not much).
Bake at 300°.
Cool, slice and eat.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper and soup.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole, place 1/2 meat mixture.
Add the potatoes and top with cheese slices.
Add remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: salad
directions: *I have used bacon bits but it is not quite as good.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spread in greased and floured square pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and butter.
Bake in 370° oven for about 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve while hot.
Very good.

title: crazy pie crust
directions: In mixer bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, shortening and water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into 9-inch pie pan.
Combine pie filling and lemon juice. Pour into middle of batter.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Divide mixture in half.
Mix half with peanut butter.
Mix half with plastic bag of coconut.
Shape into eggs and chill on wax paper.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips plus paraffin.
Dip eggs; let set until firm.

title: hoppin john
directions: Cook peas (1 part water to 1 part peas), covered with meat, chopped onion and salt and pepper to taste until peas are tender. Add more water, if needed.
Add rice, 1 tablespoon butter and red pepper (pinch). Simmer together for 15 minutes and serve.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: In saucepot, prepare fettuccine as directed.
Drain.
Return to saucepot.
Over medium-low heat, heat fettuccine, cream, butter or margarine, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Toss well. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top before serving.

title: quick-n-easy rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into lightly greased muffin pan.
Bake in hot oven (about 425°) until brown.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chicken gumbo(serves 4)
directions: Sprinkle chicken with 1/2 salt and peppers. Brown in Dutch oven. Set aside. Add okra, tomatoes and peppers to pan. Season. Add chicken stock. Cook until okra is tender, 45 to 60 minutes. Add roux. Cook 30 minutes. Add chicken and rest of salt and peppers. Cook 30 minutes. Stir in green onions and parsley. Simmer 5 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together in a large bowl.
Blend milk and cream cheese together.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Place tortilla chips in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Mix together ground beef, mushroom soup, green chiles, beans, enchilada sauce and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chips.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tutie's whole wheat bran muffins
directions: Mix and let stand 10 minutes the bran cereal and 1 cup water. Combine oil, honey, buttermilk, eggs and brown sugar.
Mix well to combine and stir in bran mixture.
Combine in very large bowl the oats, flour, salt, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, pecan pieces and raisins.
Mix the liquid and dry ingredients, stirring until well moistened.
Let batter rest 10 minutes.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 17 to 19 minutes until brown and shiny and a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse in cold water.
Set aside. Microwave (High) margarine and cream cheese in 1 1/2-quart glass bowl 20 to 30 seconds until soft.
Mix until creamy.
Blend in milk and salt.
Add noodles.
Stir and cover.
Microwave (High) 4 to 5 minutes until
heated through.
Stir twice.
Mix in Parmesan cheese.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 1 or 2 minutes until heated through.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets.
Cut tops, leaving part of stems (about 1 1/2-inches) to retain color.
Boil until soft and peel while still warm.
Place in pint jars.
Boil all other ingredients and pour over beets and seal.
Boil lids.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg, extract and black walnut flavoring.
Beat well. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add black walnuts and blend.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen (2-inch) cookies.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Bake in 2 layers or a loaf pan.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Very good with strawberries, apples, melon, etc.

title: apple butter layer cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ground cloves.
Beat butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Combine buttermilk and apple butter.
Add alternating with the flour mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely on cake rack.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Let cream cheese set out of refrigerator to get to room temperature.
Blend all ingredients together by spoon for thicker, chunkier dip or with mixer for creamier more smooth dip.
Serve as appetizer with favorite crackers (Wheat Thins are great).

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Add sugar, 3 tablespoons
at a time, until all is moist.
Mixture will be very dry.
Add
milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt; remove
from
fire.
Let
cool.
Store in refrigerator. Add more milk
for thinner sauce.
Serve over cake, ice cream or pudding. Yields 1 quart.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on greased jelly roll pan until pan is covered.
Bake as directed on roll package.
Cool.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions and cook until soft, but not brown. Add clams, broth and potatoes.
Just cover with water and cook until potatoes are cooked. Add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat until smooth.
Makes good Russian dressing with chopped sweet pickle or chopped olives added.
Refrigerate.

title: nutty cole slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar in a large bowl.
Add slaw mix, nuts and onions, if desired.
Toss and serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg and ham quiche
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan or dish.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Cook rice in 1 cup of water.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple
to
boil;
pour jello in and let stand until dissolved and
cool.
Add 2 cups buttermilk and 8 ounces Cool Whip; mix and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump
cake mix in square 8 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Dump cherries,
pineapple,
coconut
and pecans on top of cake mix. Cut butter into cubes, about 10 cubes each stick and distribute
over mix.
Bake
at 350° for about 30 minutes.	Cool and serve!

title: monkey bread
directions: In a small bowl, mix sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon, 1 cup sugar and the chopped nuts.
In another bowl, mix melted butter, 1/2 cup sugar and the other tablespoon of cinnamon.
Break apart the biscuits and roll into the first bowl of cinnamon nut mix.
Put biscuits into a greased Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter mixture over the top of the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Pour sauce over chicken mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pie pastry.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll out individual biscuits and cut in half.
Wrap around little Smokies and pinch dough together.
Bake at 375° until nicely brown.
Serve with mustard or jelly.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Heat olive oil, then saute garlic, onions and ginger.
Add all vegetables until crisp or tender.
Add soy sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix butter and Stove Top dressing mix.
Pour 1/2 mixture into bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, carrots, zucchini, onion and soup. Pour over mixture in casserole dish.
Top with remaining half of Stove Top mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and brown sugar thoroughly. Gradually add white sugar; cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir baking powder into flour; add alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla, then nuts and blend well.
Turn batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 300° for one hour and thirty minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: taco spread
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread lettuce.
Add tomatoes, black olives, onions and green peppers.
Last, spread shredded cheese.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Serve with ripple chips or nacho chips.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together, make smooth, and just one cup morsels. Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Immediately sprinkle with remaining Nestle morsels. Let stand.

title: beef, brown rice and feta casserole
directions: Put dried mushrooms in 1/2 cup hot water and let stand 20 minutes.
Saute onion in oil slowly for 5 minutes, then add tomatoes and garlic.
Cook gently, uncovered, about 10 minutes. Pepper to taste, then add dried mushrooms.
Cut in quarters if large, with any tough stems removed, and the mushroom soaking liquid.
Cook another 5 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook and peel eggplant in salted water until tender.
Drain water off.
Mash and add butter, cheese, half of cracker crumbs and onion.
Mix eggs and milk.
Add to eggplant.
Top with buttered crackers in a baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: doo-dads
directions: Mix oil, dill weed and dressing.
Pour over crackers. Mix well. Bake at 200° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix it all together, leaving some of the cheese left over to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken; bone it and cut in pieces.
Cook the spaghetti as directed; drain and saute mushrooms in butter.
Combine soup, sour cream and 1/2 cheese and mix well.
Add chicken and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamed carrots
directions: Scrape and slice carrots; cook until tender.
Drain water and put carrots in a casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over carrots. Top with bread crumbs.
Brown in medium oven.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and serve on warm hamburger buns!!

title: a sweet treat(fun for 4 to 6 year olds)
directions: Stick the main stem of the grapes into the top of the string cheese.
One by one eat the grapes and pretend it's fall.
When the grapes are all gone, it's winter and there is a big wind storm that takes off the top of the tree.
Now take the stem out of the cheese and throw it away.
Then pretend there is another wind storm and it blows the trunk away.
Now eat the cheese.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat on high speed for 5 minutes the eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured cookie pan.
Top with 1 cup crushed walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll towel and cake together (lengthwise).
Cool.
Unroll.
Spread filling on top.

title: apple-topped pork chops
directions: In a nonstick skillet, brown pork chops on both sides in oil. Place in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Add wine or broth to the skillet, stirring to loosen browned bits. Pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Butter a 10-inch tube pan.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in frosting mix until crumbly.
Set aside.
In large bowl, blend sour cream, eggs, 1/2 cup bananas and cake mix.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Fold in remaining 1 cup of bananas.
Pour 1/2 batter into pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 crumble mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool upright in pan for 30 minutes.

title: everyday easy broccoli bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can of the onions. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Top with remaining onions; bake 5 minutes.
Or, microwave, covered with waxed paper, on High for 8 minutes, rotating dish halfway through heating.
Top with remaining onions and microwave, uncovered, for 1 minute. Yields 6 servings.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Layer graham crackers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix butter, brown sugar and nuts in saucepan until melted.
Boil gently 3 minutes while stirring constantly.
Pour mixture over graham crackers. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Put back in oven a minute or two to melt chips. Take out and spread melted chocolate smooth with knife.
Cool before cutting.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Make dressing of vinegar, oil, sugar,
salt
and
curry powder and shake well.
Combine spinach,
apples,	raisins and peanuts; pour dressing over and serve.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks with cold water until frothy.
In separate bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs with sugar and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to the egg yolks.
Add vanilla.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cracker mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare and cut up potatoes into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in plastic bag. Moisten potatoes in water and
put in bag.
Shake a few times in bag until potatoes are well coated with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place potatoes in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once when golden brown.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine Kool-Aid and sugar.
Cream in the cream cheese with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip, a little at a time.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Serve with apples, bananas and strawberries.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies(makes 3 dozen.)
directions: Mix flour with baking soda. Combine margarine, the sugars & pudding mix in large bowl; beat until smooth & creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture, stir in oats & raisins (batter will be stiff).
Drop from rounded tablespoons on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 min.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Dip tablespoon in sugar.
Place on greased sheet.
Sprinkle with 2 to 3 drops of water.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until toothpick clean.

title: quick supper dish
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add milk, soup and meat.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add sugar, oil, salt and egg.
Stir to dissolve sugar and salt.
Stir in 1 cup flour until smooth.
Cover bowl and place over pan of warm water for 15 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir down batter and add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Stir and turn out.
Knead 3 minutes (add 1/4 cup flour, if needed).
Divide into 16 pieces and shape into rolls.
Arrange in pan.
Brush with butter.
Cover and place over pan of warm water for 25 minutes.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Mix white grape juice, ginger ale and crushed grapes together. Chill in freezer until slushy.

title: rhubarb 'n' dumplings
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine 1 1/4 cups water, brown sugar, 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and the 3 tablespoons butter.
Add the sliced rhubarb. Microcook, uncovered, on High for 7 to 9 minutes or until mixture is thickened and bubbly, stirring after every minute.
Cover casserole to keep warm.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 8-inch pan.
To melted, slightly cooled shortening add brown sugar.
Stir in eggs. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into pan and bake 25 minutes.
Do not overbake! Cool or serve warm.

title: cobbler
directions: Use any kind of fruit in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble ingredients until fine and sprinkle evenly over top of fruit.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick microwave fudge
directions: Sift the powdered sugar and cocoa into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass pan.
Pour in milk and place butter on top.
Do not mix.
Cook for 2 minutes in microwave; remove and stir just to mix ingredients. Add vanilla and nuts; stir until well blended.
Freeze for 20 minutes or refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all thoroughly; form into walnut size balls.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
