Serve immediately or store and serve as follows:
cool sausage balls.
Place in freezer bags and freeze.
Do not thaw.
Place on ungreased baking sheets and bake at 325° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Do not microwave.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix all dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Stir until just blended.
Bake in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: krispie bars
directions: In large pan, melt margarine.
Add marshmallows.
Cook and stir until melted.
Stir in peanut butter.
Immediately stir in cereal and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish lightly sprayed with Pam.
Melt some chocolate chips on low heat with a little water until the proper consistency to drizzle it.
Drizzle over warm bars.

title: diabetic squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into two shells.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: triple chocolate brownies
directions: Make pudding according to package directions. Stir in dry cake mix. Spread in greased jelly roll pan or 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with chips. Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 pan for 30 minutes or in 11 x 15-inch pan for 20 minutes.

title: double baked potatoes
directions: Wash and bake potatoes in a 425° oven until done.
Split top and scoop out and place in large mixing bowl.
Mash and add other ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Pile in shells and refrigerate until ready to bake.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb pinwheels
directions: Combine 1 1/2 c. sugar, 1 1/2 c. water and cook for five minutes. Pour into greased rectangular pan. Make biscuit dough by sifting together flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar. Cut in crisco. Add milk and stir lightly. Knead on floured board briefly. Roll into a
12 inch square, 1/3 inch thick. Brush with 3 Tbsp. melted butter.

Cover dough with rhubarb and roll up as a jelly roll. Cut into 1 1/2 slices and place in syrup in pan. Bake in a hot oven 450 degrees for 40 minutes or until baked through. During baking, baste with sauce made by cooking together 1 cup of rhubarb, 1/2 c. sugar and 2/3 c. water.

title: cherry pie
directions: In bowl, stir together sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice, vanilla and almond flavoring until mixed.
Fold in Dream Whip (whipped).
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with 1 can Comstock cherry pie filling.
Can use blueberry, strawberry, etc.

title: mexican stuff
directions: Beta 4 eggs well.
Add 2 cans chopped green chilies.
Add 1/4 cup jalapenos (seeded and chopped).
Add cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: perfect dills
directions: Boil
ingredients 15 minutes.
Pack cucumbers
in
jars with lots of dill
and
teaspoon
whole
black pepper and garlic if you wish.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar to each quart, but do not boil the sugar.
Pour boiling vinegar brine over cukes. Fill to tops of
jars
and	seal
tight.
Set
jars in boiling water to come over the
top of them.
Let stand in there until cold.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon and add brown sugar, vinegar, water and flour. Stir until thickened.
Layer potatoes with raw onions.
Pour bacon mixture over all.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt together butter and peanut butter.
Then add crackers and sugar.
Mix and then press together into a greased cookie sheet. Melt chips and spread over bars.
Refrigerate to set awhile.

title: debbie's breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain well.
Separate and roll out dough into 16 triangles.
Press over bottom and up sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press perforated edges together to seal and form a crust.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with hash browns.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, water and seasonings.
Pour over pan contents.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil hen in pot with 2 quarts of water until tender.
Remove from pan and remove bones.
Either chop or grind chicken and return to pot.
Add to pot before deboning the chicken.
Cook onion and tomatoes with meat 30 minutes on low.
Add corn, stirring to keep from sticking; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add soda and hot sauce, if desired.
Serve at once.
Excellent for cold weather.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Combine all ingredients in large deep bowl.
Marinate the roast at least 24 hours, turning roast at least once.

title: self frosting date cake
directions: Pour boiling water and 1 teaspoon soda over dates; set aside. Cream together the sugar, 3/4 teaspoon soda, shortening, salt and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add date mixture and flour.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add half of flour and mix with mixer.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Add remaining flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour in tube pan or Bundt pan at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Make crepes from very thin pancake batter with small teaspoon sugar added.
Do this by tilting small frying pan and running batter all over bottom of pan (sprayed with Pam).
Put 2 tablespoons of vanilla ice cream along middle of crepes.
Wrap around ice cream and freeze for 30 to 40 minutes.
Take from freezer and pour hot sweetened strawberries and juice over crepes.
Heat in microwave for about 20 seconds.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cajun spiced chicken
directions: In 3-quart rectangular baking dish, combine all ingredients but chicken.
Mix well.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Arrange in a single layer.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until tender in 350° oven.
Serve chicken and pan drippings with hot cooked rice.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a large pan. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Mix in oats and peanut butter.
Stir until mixed well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Gradually add Cool Whip and 10x sugar until smooth.
Spoon filling into crusts and freeze 8 hours.
When ready to serve, top with chocolate shavings.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Place fillets in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with vegetables and garlic.
Blend chicken broth and tomato sauce and pour over fillets.
Sprinkle with oregano and pepper.
Pour olive oil over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: tuna-cheese casserole
directions: Prepare Kraft dinner as package directs.
Combine with peas, tuna, soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired, cover with buttered crumbs or crushed potato chips during last 15 minutes of baking.

title: onion pie
directions: Crush crackers and pour melted margarine over them; mix well. Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Saute** onions in 2 tablespoons of margarine until clear.
Place onions in pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over onions.
Grate cheese over all and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage cacciatore
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Arrange cabbage on top of meat mixture.
Blend spaghetti sauce and garlic salt; pour over cabbage.
Cover tightly; bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover for a few minutes to melt cheese.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together, folding in whipped topping last. Pour into 9-inch pan. Freeze. Cut into squares to serve.

title: aunt gladys' asparagus casserole
directions: In a small baking pan, lay the asparagus flat.
Layer 1/2 can soup over asparagus.
Layer 1/2 c. grated cheese on top of this. Add drained peas, then remaining soup on top of peas.
Place remaining cheese on last.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Sprinkle almonds over top and continue baking for 5 minutes more until almonds are slightly brown.

title: chex tuna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In bowl, combine egg, mayonnaise, dry mustard, salt, pepper, onion and green pepper.
Stir in Chex crumbs.
Mix in tuna.
Press gently into 8-inch pie plate with spoon.
Shape to fit like a pastry shell.
Toss vegetables with 1/4 cup cheese.
Turn into shell.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over vegetables.
Bake 25 minutes or microwave on High 5 minutes or until crust is firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together pudding and milk until blended.
Add Cool Whip and beat with electric mixer at high speed until thick.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place a layer of whole graham crackers.
On top of crackers, place 1/2 of pudding mixture.
To the top of this, add another layer of crackers.
Add remaining pudding mixture and top with a final layer of crackers.
Chill for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ice with milk chocolate icing.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Mix together.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into yolk mixture.
Spread over cheese and chile mix.
Push in with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Slice tomatoes last 30 minutes.

title: million dollar relish
directions: Grind cukes, onions and peppers.
Add water and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.

title: grilled pork kabobs
directions: Cut tenderloin in pieces, approximately 1-inch wide.
Slice sausage in 1/2-inch slices.
Clean and trim mushrooms.
Cut onions and pepper in 1-inch pieces.

title: instant potato soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in air-tight container.
To make soup, add 1/4 cup of the mixture to 1 cup of boiling water. Let stand for 1 or 2 minutes before eating.

title: pearl's chicken
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Cut up boneless chicken into bite-size pieces (enough to cover the bottom of dish).
Empty soup into bowl and add 1/2 cup of milk.
Mix until smooth.
Spread soup over chicken.
Cover soup mixture with 1 cup stuffing.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and pour over stuffing mix.
Cover and bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: moma sue's cookies
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil, then line with crackers. Melt the butter with the brown sugar. Boil for 3 minutes.
Heat oven to 400° and pour brown sugar and butter over crackers. Bake 5 minutes. Remove from oven and when it stops bubbling, pour the chocolate chips over the crackers.
When they melt, spread with a knife. Cool and break into squares.

title: homemade lasagne
directions: You will need
2 large lasagne pans.
Use large pan lightly sprayed with Pam.
Cook 1 pound of lasagne noodles following package directions.
Drain when done.
Heat spaghetti sauce. Layer in this order:

title: apple-rice breakfast
directions: Wash rice and drain; combine with water and salt to taste in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer.
Simmer, loosely covered, 45 minutes.
Rice should be tender and most of the liquid absorbed.
Let stand for 5 minutes; drain.

title: david's corn bread
directions: Wash the figs in lukewarm water.
Discard water.
Leave the skins on the fruit and a short portion of the stem so the juices remain inside the fig.
(This procedure also helps figs retain their shape throughout cooking.)
Place the figs inside a large bowl or pot filled with the sugar.
Let stand for at least 24 hours.
(Figs make their own juices, somewhat like strawberries.)

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove pan from heat.
Beat eggs, sugar and vinegar with a fork until blended.
Add the egg mixture to the bacon drippings and blend with a spoon.
Return the pan to low heat and stir constantly until thick.
Overcooking will cause separation.
Pour hot mixture over spinach, endive or lettuce.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, onion, egg, crumbled bread slice, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Put in
a loaf pan.
Place wax paper over pan. Place in microwave and cook on High for 5 minutes. Take pan out and drain fat.
Place back in microwave with no covering and cook on High for 15 minutes.
Check to be sure it is cooked through.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease only bottoms of muffin pan cups or spray muffin pan with nonstick spray.
In medium bowl with fork, stir milk, egg and oil until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients and stir just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 4 days.

title: peachy ice cream pie
directions: Drain peaches; save syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup. Heat to boiling.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Cut ice cream into 6 pieces.
Add to hot liquid.
Stir until melted.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon (15 to 20 minutes).
Leave
a few
peaches out for top of pie.
Fold in rest of peaches.
Pour into shell.
Chill until firm. Top with whipped cream and peaches.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and brush onto burgers, ribs, chicken, chops or steaks.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Combine spinach and onion.
Cook as spinach package directs. Drain well.
Combine eggs, cheeses, salad dressing, butter or margarine and garlic powder.
Add spinach mixture and muffin mix; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Chill until serving time (or place in a freezer container, seal, label and freeze).

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put 1 cup crushed corn flakes in buttered dish.
Add shredded cabbage, sliced water chestnuts, and onion.
Over this pour a mixture of butter, cream of celery soup, milk, mayonnaise, and grated cheese.
Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into each cone or half full.
Set in oblong pan.
Bake as directed on cake box for cupcakes.
Let cool.
Ice and decorate.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best-ever yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
and
teaspoons
sugar in 1 cup warm water. Let
stand
about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining sugar, salt, butter and shortening in large bowl.
Add boiling water, stirring until
butter
and
shortening melt.
Cool slightly. Add dissolved
yeast,
stirring
well.
Add
eggs
and 3 cups flour, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth. Stir in remaining
flour
to make soft dough.
Place in well-greased bowl, turning
to
grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until double in bulk.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Place in bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over hamburger.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs together until smooth.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 5 quart dutch oven over high heat, heat first four ingredients, 4 c. water and 1 Tbsp. salt to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 35 minutes, or until chicken is fork tender.
When chicken is done, reserve 1 c.
broth.
(Freeze remaining broth).
Cool chicken slightly; remove and discard bones and skin.
Cut meat into 1 inch pieces.
In 3 quart saucepan over high heat, heat carrots, celery, onions and reserved 1 c. chicken broth to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Remove vegetables to small bowl, leaving broth in sauce pan.
In small bowl, with fork, blend flour with 3/4 c. half and half; gradually stir into broth in saucepan until smooth.
Stir in remaining half and half.
Over low heat; cook, stirring consistly until sauce is thickened.
Stir in chicken, cooked vegetables, mixed vegetables, mushrooms and 1 3/4 tsp. salt.
Spoon chicken mixture into 9 X 13 baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pastry.
On lightly floured rolling pin, roll dough to 10 X 14 rectangle.
Place pastry loosely over filling.
Trim edge with 1 inch overhang. Fold overhang under, making a high standing edge.
In small bowl mix egg yolk with 1 tsp. water.
Brush pastry with egg mixture. Bake 1 hour or until crust is golden and mixture is hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: venison meat balls
directions: Put meat, eggs, spices and cheese into a bowl.
Wet the 3 slices of bread and squeeze dry.
Shred into meat and mix.
Form into balls (egg size).
Slightly flatten.
Roll in bread crumbs. Cook in oil until nicely browned.
Drop meat balls into boiling pasta sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: one cup of everything cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl, then roll into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: pretzel strawberry
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: au gratin potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until partially done. Combine soup, milk and cheese. Alternate layers of potatoes and soup mixture in a buttered baking pan, adding salt and pepper as you go. Add dash of paprika. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and top with partially crumbled onion rings. Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: cranberry nut bread #2
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add remainder of ingredients; blend until all ingredients are wet.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Let stand overnight before cutting.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in skillet.
Simmer a few minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: 3-quart broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw frozen broccoli.
Saute onions in margarine.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add powdered sugar slowly until enough to spread.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Place peach halves, open side up, in the pie shell.
Fill center of each peach with chopped nuts.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over the peaches.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 325° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: caramel corn(non-sticky)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from stove.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda (will foam).
Stir. Pour mixture over popped corn. Stir. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir once.
If not all eaten, this will keep well in the freezer.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix warm butter and sugar well.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift in 2 cups flour, salt and spices.
Add nuts and fruits that have been cut up with scissors and mixed well with one cup of flour.
Last, add dissolved soda.
Drop with teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake around 20 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: forever ambers
directions: Combine all ingredients (except sugar).
Spread mixture into lightly oiled 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 275°. Remove from oven.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon. Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: candy
directions: Bring the oleo, butter and sugar to a boil; boil 2 minutes. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Arrange graham crackers on foil.
Cover with pecans.
Spoon sauce over pecans.
Bake for 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Good and rich.

title: fish in dill sauce
directions: Peel cucumber and then cut longways.
Then seed the center of the cucumber and chop.
Mix first 4 ingredients and let set in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; add cocoa.
Alternately add eggs and flour.
Add vanilla and nuts; spread into a large pan.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Spread over chocolate mixture and swirl through chocolate.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Chop up all ingredients.
Use as little or as much as you want.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Use with tortilla chips as dip.
Good and quick!

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: spanish omelet sauce
directions: Saute vegetables in butter about 5 minutes.
Add rest and simmer about 10 minutes.
Make one day before serving, then heat thoroughly.
Leftovers may be frozen.

title: salsa
directions: Boil 30 minutes; put into jars and heat in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened. Beat with mixer 2 minutes (medium speed).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: sauce for banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar and flour well.
Add eggs, butter and vanilla. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Use whites of eggs for topping.

title: potato casserole
directions: Wash, peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Mix pepper, onion and salt.
Spread over potatoes.
Mix mushroom soup with milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 425° until potatoes are done.
Dot top of casserole during baking.

title: amanda's coffee cake
directions: Mix sifted flour with sugar and cinnamon.
With mixer, blend egg, milk, oil and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and continue to simmer, stirring frequently, until most of the liquid is evaporated and carrots are tender and glazed.
If a thicker glaze is desired, add 2 teaspoons of cornstarch to 1/4 cup of water.
Stir until combined and add to carrots; continue cooking until sauce is desired thickness.

title: garden herb cheese spread
directions: Use all of the ingredients as given or to taste.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in small amount of butter or nonstick spray.
Add beef tips and simmer on low heat.
Pour gravy over mixture and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: stewed zucchini
directions: Chop zucchini into bite size pieces.
Boil until tender.
Chop tomatoes into bite size pieces and cook into zucchini.
Add other chopped ingredients and spices to taste.
Serve hot.

title: banana bread with peanut frosting
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, rum extract, vanilla, bananas and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour into pan and bake for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly and spread Peanut Frosting while still warm.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: ranch salad
directions: Combine vegetables, bacon and cheese in a large bowl.
Combine salad dressings; pour over salad and toss to mix.

title: earl's cookies
directions: Blend thoroughly the first 7 ingredients.
Add the flour and baking soda and cream well.
Add pecan pieces, chocolate morsels and coconut flakes.
Blend together well.
Add quick-cooking oats and mix together.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: greek delight
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Make a dressing with vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Combine and chill in refrigerator or serve at room temperature.

title: green beans and potatoes
directions: Heat butter in saucepan with tight lid.
Cook onion until soft.
Stir in beans; mix well.
Place sliced potatoes over beans. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until beans and potatoes are tender.
If extra moisture is needed, add hot water, one tablespoon at a time.

title: easy candy recipe
directions: Simply combine semi-sweet chocolate with sweetened condensed milk.
Heat the mixture on top of stove or in microwave, stirring frequently, just until chocolate is melted and mixture can be thoroughly combined.
Remove chocolate from heat and stir in your choice of nuts, raisins or cereal.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and let set until firm.
May be stored in covered bowl, box or tin for up to 2 weeks at room temperature.

title: apple crisp
directions: Measure dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix in shortening as for pie crust.
Add egg yolk mixture.
Mix together.
Roll out 1/2 of dough to fit large cookie sheet.
Top crust with apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Roll out other half of dough for top crust.
Pinch edges of 2 crusts together.
Beat egg white stiff and spread on crust with pastry brush.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.
Glaze immediately after taking out of oven with powdered sugar and water.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Spray 9 X 13 pan with Pam. Cut up stale bread in squares and cover bottom of pan. Brown sausage until crumbly. Sprinkle sausage over bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Beat eggs, milk and salt (could add some chives and thyme also). Pour over sausage and cheese, cover and place in refrigerator overnight. Next morning bake at 350° for 30 min. Serves 6 - 8.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until crumbly.
Break egg into a one-cup measure.
Add lemon juice; beat together with a fork.
Finish filling cup with water.
Pour over flour mixture and stir with fork.
Roll out crust on floured board.
Makes 7 crusts.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Pack brown sugar in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle whipping cream over brown sugar.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over top.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Sprinkle cinnamon to taste.
Cut biscuits into quarters and place on top (do not cut into quarters completely).
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Turn over.
Brown sugar will drizzle over biscuits.

title: lady baltimore fresh coconut cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken skillet
directions: Place chicken in skillet; salt and pepper according to taste. Pour Coke and tomato sauce over chicken.
Place lid on skillet; cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holiday cheese tarts
directions: In large mixing bowl, cut together flour, oleo and cheese until mixture clings together.
Form into a ball.
On floured surface, roll out dough to form a 12 x 10-inch rectangle. Starting with a short end, fold in half.
Repeat rolling out and folding 4 more times.
Roll out dough to make a 15 x 11-inch rectangle.
Using star shape cutter, cut out cookies and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Press indentation in center, filled with choice of jam, preserves or marmalade.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
Remove; cool on wire racks.
Drizzle with icing.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Slightly beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 325° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake about 30 more minutes.

title: shortbread("shorty")
directions: Do not use margarine!

title: crepes
directions: Combine flour, eggs, melted butter, salt and milk in food processor until smooth.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Cook crepes in omelette pan.
Butter when cooked.
Can be filled with any assortment of fillings.
Example: cream cheese and sausage crepes are very good!

title: seafood salad(main dish)
directions: Place 3 cups water in a saucepan with salt; bring to a boil. Add thawed shrimp.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 to 3 minutes after water returns to a boil.
Drain and rinse in cold water to cool. Peel and devein.

title: herbed new potatoes
directions: Peel 1/2 inch strip around the center of each potato and place in a medium saucepan of cold water. Add enough additional water to the pan to cover the potatoes by 2 inches. Bring to a boil over medium -high heat. Boil until the potatoes are tender, drain. Cover to keep warm. Melt butter and stir in parsley, chives and onion soup mix. Mix well. Pour the butter mixture over potatoes and toss to coat. Sprinkle parsley for garnish if desired. Serve immediately.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Pinch the bread in a medium bowl.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Mix until mixture will hold together to make patties.
Make patties and flour each side and brown on each side.
Make gravy with boiling water and add bouillon cubes.
Stir until cubes melt.
Take cornstarch mixed with milk or water to make a thin paste.
Turn the bouillon broth and add the paste slowly into it.
Put browned patties in a greased baking dish.
Pour gravy over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread thaw (don't let it rise!).
Follow package directions.
Put a little oil on cookie sheet per loaf.
Roll out flat to fit the cookie sheet (thin is best).
Put a layer of ham, then cheese, then the pepperoni.
Roll up dough into a long loaf, like French bread.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain juice from cans and in a large bowl, mix together all vegetables.
Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Cool quickly in ice water.
Pour cooled liquid over vegetable mixture and chill overnight.
May be kept in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: macaroni-cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients while macaroni is still hot.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/3 of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine caramels, milk and margarine in a double boiler until blended, stirring often.
Pour over first layer of baked cake.
Pour rest of batter over caramel layer and sprinkle with chips and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, frost with Cool Whip.

title: duck blood soup
directions: Cover duck with water in large kettle.
Add salt.
Bring to boil.
Skim off foam.
Put vegetables and spices into a cheesecloth bag and add to soup.
Cover and continue boiling for an hour.
Remove spice bag.
Remove meat; remove bones and chop meat.
Return it to the soup.
Add dried fruit and cook for 30 minutes.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Put egg, sugar, oil, molasses, All-Bran and milk into mixing bowl and let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to bran mixture.
Mix only until moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: st. patrick's day cupcakes
directions: Grease muffin cups or line with paper bake cups.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, pudding mix, chocolate pieces, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, combine beaten eggs, milk, oil and vanilla or almond extract.
Stir into flour mixture just until combined.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Makes 18.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting; sprinkle with green sugar. Can then add green M&M's.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine hamburger, rice, salt, pepper and onions.
Form into balls.
Heat soup and water.
Drop meat balls into liquid.
Boil until tender.
Great with mashed potatoes.

title: canadian snowflakes
directions: Beat butter at medium speed until creamy.
Gradually add flour. Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch round cookie cutter right on cookie sheet.
Remove excess dough from cookie sheet.
Using a drinking straw, randomly cut holes in dough, removing dough by slight twisting of the straw.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Cool the chicken and pick off bones; cut meat (not too fine). If mixture is too thick and dry, add more broth.
Sprinkle some crumbs on the top and bake until golden brown.

title: ground beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in oil.
Mix in onion, salt, pepper and rice.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add soup and water; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Spoon cabbage into 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture over cabbage to completely cover cabbage.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: eggs and stuff
directions: Place 8 slices of bread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with small chunks of ham and sharp cheese.
Place 8 more slices on top.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Saut chopped onions.
Brown and drain hamburger meat and mix in onions.
Add tomato sauce, beans, salt, chili powder and ketchup.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Stir in M&M's.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Top of cookies will look pale.)
Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then remove.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and mix with next 6 ingredients.
Blend in soup and milk.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes at 425°.

title: lemon sugar snaps
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in small bowl.
In large bowl cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and lemon rind, extract and juice.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Wrap dough in plastic and chill dough overnight.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, eggs, flour and buttermilk.
Add in food coloring, cocoa, salt, vanilla, vinegar and soda.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: very smooth cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: red rice
directions: Smother vegetables with 2 tablespoons oil.
Season with salt, bell pepper, red pepper and Worcestershire.
Cook slowly until almost dry.
Add rice and stir with a fork to mix.
Cook until dry.
To the mixture, add bacon, ham, shrimp, crawfish or crabmeat.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in rolled oats and nuts.
Mix.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheets (1 tablespoon of dough).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cocoa peanut squares
directions: Combine corn syrup and brown sugar in a medium saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until the mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Add Cocoa Crispies, stirring until well coated with mixture.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares when cooled.

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and place triangles on a 12 inch pizza pan, forming a ring with pointed ends facing outer edge of a pan and wide ends overlapping. Lightly press wide ends together.

title: peppernuts
directions: Beat eggs with powdered sugar for 30 minutes, between low and medium on electric mixer.
Add the other ingredients and mix well. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: low-fat yeast rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt mixture and egg whites.
Combine flour and salt.
Stir 2 cups flour mixture into yogurt mixture.
Stir or beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually stir in remaining flour mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Punch dough down, roll out on floured surface and shape as desired.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in warm place which is free from drafts until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon regular Crisco in cast-iron frypan to smoking.
Salt
and
pepper
both sides of each chop (rub in). Slide
each
chop
into hot grease and keep moving until it is seared
enough
to not stick to bottom.
Sear until very light brown,
then turn and do other sides.
Leave on each side only until
very
light	brown, don't fry chops.
Take chops out of pan and
drain
on plate.

title: all-in-one casserole
directions: Steam hamburger, onion and peppers until red is gone from meat; add peas, carrots, rice and celery soup.
Place in casserole dish; top with onion rings.
Bake in oven at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: english peas casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 275° until hot.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Blend well in blender.

title: saturday night supper
directions: Soak limas overnight or early in morning.
Cook until tender; pour into casserole, saving the liquor that's left.
Mix mustard, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar thoroughly through the beans. Top with slices of sausage meat and bake in moderate oven for an hour or until meat is nicely browned.
Use the reserved liquor to keep beans from getting too dry during baking, if needed.

title: slush
directions: Bring sugar and 7 cups water to a boil.
Let green tea bags steep in 2 cups boiling water for 10 minutes.
Combine sugar water with steeped tea; stir in frozen concentrates.
Add liquor. Freeze, stirring a few times before mixture becomes solid.
To serve, fill glasses with half slush, half 7-Up or 50-50.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits, then put in casserole dish.
Add other ingredients and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Combine ingredients and pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir three times to keep mixture crumbly. Line 9 x 13-inch cake pan with 2/3 of mixture and reserve 1/3 for topping.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Put in buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix in chicken soup.
Drop Cheez Whiz by spoonfuls on top.
Cover and bake 1/2 hour at 325°.
Remove cover and top with onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes uncovered.

title: old fashioned freezer ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well, add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly. Add Milnot.
Add milk.
Freeze.

title: limas in sour cream
directions: Cook limas in boiling, salted water until tender (about 20 minutes); drain.
Saute onion and pimento in butter until tender. Stir in limas, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until well heated (about 15 minutes).

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.
Add milk and yeast; mix.
Cover and refrigerate until cold.
Roll out on floured surface; cut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes in preheated 450° oven.
Dough may be stored in refrigerator for over a week.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix well and bake in three layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot souffle(better than sweet potatoes)
directions: Combine in blender.
Pour into baking dish.
May garnish with a mixture of 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake for 90 minutes at 350°.

title: poppycock
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup together.
Bring to boil. Boil until it turns light caramel in color, about 15 minutes. Add vanilla. Pour over popcorn and nuts. Spread out onto greased waxed paper. Press to make a thin layer.
After cooled, break up into pieces.
